igned\n| 29 April 2007<ref>{{cite news |title=Allardyce resigns as Bolton boss |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/b/bolton_wanderers/6605673.stm|publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 April 2007|accessdate=29 April 2007}}</ref>\n| 5th\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Sammy Lee (footballer)|Sammy Lee]]\n| 30 April 2007<ref>{{cite news |title=Lee appointed manager of Bolton |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/b/bolton_wanderers/6606553.stm|publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 April 2007|accessdate=30 April 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Glenn Roeder]]\n| 6 May 2007<ref>{{cite news |title=Roeder resigns as Newcastle boss |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/n/newcastle_united/6630751.stm|publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 May 2007|accessdate=6 May 2007}}</ref>\n| 13th\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Nigel Pearson]] <small>(caretaker)</small>\n| 6 May 2007\n|}\n\n==League table==\n{{see also|Premier League#Competition}}\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|show_limit=5\n\n|team1=MUN|name_MUN=[[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]\n|team2=CHE|name_CHE=[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|team3=LIV|name_LIV=[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|team4=ARS|name_ARS=[[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]\n|team5=TOT|name_TOT=[[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]\n|team6=EVE|name_EVE=[[Everton F.C.|Everton]]\n|team7=BOL|name_BOL=[[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n|team8=REA|name_REA=[[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n|team9=POR|name_POR=[[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]]\n|team10=BLB|name_BLB=[[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]\n|team11=AST|name_AST=[[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]\n|team12=MID|name_MID=[[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]\n|team13=NEW|name_NEW=[[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n|team14=MCI|name_MCI=[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n|team15=WHU|name_WHU=[[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n|team16=FUL|name_FUL=[[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]\n|team17=WIG|name_WIG=[[Wigan