al (b. 1889)\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Frank Jarvis]], American runner and triple jumper (b. 1878)\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Louis Vierne]], French organist and composer (b. 1870)\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Lou Gehrig]], American baseball player (b. 1903)\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Bunny Berigan]], American singer and trumpet player (b. 1908)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[John Gretton, 1st Baron Gretton]], English sailor and politician (b. 1867)\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Viktor Brack]], German physician (b. 1904)\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Karl Brandt]], German [[SS]] officer (b. 1904)\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Karl Gebhardt]], German physician (b. 1897)\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Waldemar Hoven]], German physician (b. 1903)\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Wolfram Sievers]], German [[SS]] officer (b. 1905)\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Naum Torbov]], Bulgarian architect, designed the [[Central Sofia Market Hall]] (b. 1880)\n*[[1956]] &ndash; [[Jean Hersholt]], Danish-American actor and director (b. 1886)\n*[[1959]] &ndash; [[Lyda Borelli]], Italian actress (b. 1884)\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[George S. Kaufman]], American director, producer, and playwright (b. 1889)\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Vita Sackville-West]], English author and poet (b. 1892)<ref>{{cite web |title=Vita Sackville-West {{!}} British writer |url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/V-Sackville-West |website=Encyclopedia Britannica |accessdate=27 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Benno Ohnesorg]], German student and activist (b. 1940)\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Andr\u00e9 Mathieu]], Canadian pianist and composer (b. 1929)\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Leo Gorcey]], American actor (b. 1917)\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Orhan Kemal]], Turkish author (b. 1914)\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Albert Lamorisse]], French director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1922)\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Bruce McLaren]], New Zealand race car driver and engineer, founded the [[McLaren|McLaren racing team]] (b. 1937)\n*  1970   &ndash; [[Giuseppe Ungaretti]], Italian soldier, journalist, and academic (b. 1888)\n*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Hiroshi Kazato]], Japanese race car driver (b. 1949)\n*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Kenneth Mason (geographer)|Kenneth Mason]], English soldier and geographer (b. 1887)\n*  1976   &ndash; [[Juan Jos\u00e9 Torres]], Bolivian general and politician, 61st [[President of Bolivia]] (b. 1920)\n*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Albert Bittlmayer]], German footballer (b. 1952)\n*  1977   &ndash; [[Stephen Boyd]], Northern Irish-born American actor (b. 1931)\n*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Santiago Bernab\u00e9u Yeste]], Spanish footballer and coach (b. 1895)\n*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Jim Hutton]], American actor (b. 1934)\n*[[1982]] &ndash; [[Fazal Ilahi Chaudhry]], Pakistani lawyer and politician, 5th [[President of Pakistan]] (b. 1904)\n*[[1983]] &ndash; [[Stan Rogers]], Canadian singer-songwriter (b. 1949)\n*  1983   &ndash; [[Ray Stehr]], Australian rugby league player and coach (b. 1913)\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Aur\u00e8le Joliat]], Canadian ice hockey player (b. 1901)\n*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Anthony de Mello]], Indian-American priest and psychotherapist (b. 1931)\n*  1987   &ndash; [[Sammy Kaye]], American bandleader and songwriter (b. 1910)\n*  1987   &ndash; [[Andr\u00e9s Segovia]], Spanish guitarist (b. 1893)\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[Raj Kapoor]], Indian actor, director, and producer (b. 1924)\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Ted a'Beckett]], Australian cricketer and footballer (b. 1907)\n*[[1990]] &ndash; [[Jack Gilford]], American actor and comedian (b. 1908)\n*  1990   &ndash; [[Rex Harrison]], English actor (b. 1908)\n*[[1991]] &ndash; [[Ahmed Arif]], Turkish poet and author (b. 1927)\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Philip Dunne (writer)|Philip Dunne]], American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1908)\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Johnny Mize]], American baseball player, coach, and sportscaster (b. 1913)\n*  1993   &ndash; [[Tahar Djaout]], Algerian journalist, writer and poet (b. 1954)\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[David Stove]], Australian philosopher, author, and academic (b. 1927)\n*[[1996]] &ndash; [[John Alton]], Hungarian-