{"title_page": "List of candidates in the 2016 Philippine presidential election", "text_new": "This is a list of '''candidates in the [[2016 Philippine presidential election|Philippine presidential and vice presidential elections of 2016]]''' {{As of|2016|05|02|df=US|lc=y}}.\n\n==Candidates for President==\nThese are people who submitted candidacies, and were allowed to run by the Commission on Elections and to be included in ballots.\n\n===Jejomar Binay===\n{{main|Jejomar Binay presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Jejomar Binay.jpg|upright|thumb|Jejomar Binay]]\nWhen he was questioned by the media at the [[Coconut Palace]] in September 2011, Vice President [[Jejomar Binay]] ([[United Nationalist Alliance|UNA]]) confirmed his plans to run for president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/13/11/binay-run-president-2016|title=Binayaran wants to run for president in 2016|first=Atom|last=Araullo|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=September 13, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nBy May 2014, Binay began his search for a running mate. As his potential running mate Senator [[Jinggoy Estrada]] in jail due to his implication in the [[Priority Development Assistance Fund scam|PDAF scam]],<ref name=\"Macaraig\">{{cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/53457-jinggoy-support-machinery-2016-bid|title = Jinggoy: I still have support, machinery for 2016|first = Ayee|last = Macaraig|work = Rappler|date = March 20, 2014}}</ref> Binay's offers were declined by [[JV Ejercito]],<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/22/14/jv-rules-out-running-binays-vice-cites-same-skin-color|title = JV rules out running as Binay's vice, cites same skin color|first = Willard|last = Cheng|work = [[Philippine Star]]|date = 2014-05-22|accessdate = 2014-06-08}}</ref> [[Manny Villar]] (via wife [[Cynthia Villar]]),<ref name=\"Rappler.com\">{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/76220-manny-villar-2016-plans|title = Manny Villar for VP? 'Never,' says wife|last = |first = |date = 2014-11-06|work = Rappler.com|access-date = 2015-06-07|via = }}</ref> [[Vilma Santos]] (via husband [[Ralph Recto]]),<ref>{{cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/581945/vilma-santos-has-no-plans-for-2016-might-retire-from-politics-sen-recto<|title = Vilma has no plans for 2016, might retire from politics\u2014Sen. Recto|first = Matikas|last = Santos|work = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-03-03|accessdate = 2015-05-13}}</ref> [[Mar Roxas]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = Roxas not even thinking of being VP Binay's running mate in 2016|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/467754/news/nation/roxas-not-even-thinking-of-being-vp-binay-s-running-mate-in-2016|accessdate = 2015-06-22|date = 2015-04-10|website = GMA News Online}}</ref> [[Grace Poe]],<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/490374/news/nation/grace-poe-doesn-t-see-herself-as-vp-binay-s-running-mate|title = Grace Poe doesn't see herself as VP Binay's running mate|first = Johanna Camille|last = Sisante|work = GMA News Online|date = May 20, 2015|accessdate = 2015-05-24}}</ref> [[Rodrigo Duterte]]<ref name=\"duterte may23\">{{cite news|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/23/15/duterte-i-wont-run-national-post-2016|title = Duterte: I won't run for national post in 2016|work = ABS-CBNnews.com|date = 2015-05-23|accessdate = 2015-05-23}}</ref> and [[Joseph Estrada]].<ref name=\"Clapano\">{{Cite web|title = Erap not interested in running for VP|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/06/07/1463063/erap-not-interested-running-vp|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2015-06-07|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|publisher = |last = Clapano|first = Jose Rodel}}</ref> Binay's daughter [[Abigail Binay|Abigail]], also the Representative from Makati, said that Binay would accept anyone as his running mate except for [[Antonio Trillanes]], and that she prefers [[Grace Poe]], however Sen. [[Bongbong Marcos]] was the most preferred by UNA officials to be his running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Binay's running mate 'anyone but Trillanes'|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/05/19/1456467/binays-running-mate-anyone-trillanes|accessdate = 2015-06-22|date = 2015-05-19|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|first = Patricia Lourdes|publisher = |last = Viray}}</ref> In a 2015 Independence Day (June 12) speech in [[Iloilo]], President Aquino said that he could only offer Binay the conduct of a clean and honest election, but not an outright endorsement.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Mar gets Noy's praise but still no endorsement|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/06/13/1465293/mar-gets-noys-praise-still-no-endorsement|accessdate = 2015-06-13|date = 2015-06-13|website = [[The Philippine Star]]}}</ref>\n\nA few days later, on June 22, Binay resigned from the Aquino cabinet, both as presidential adviser on [[Overseas Filipino Workers]]' concerns and as chairman of the Housing and Urban Development Coordinating Council, but did not say why.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Fed up, Binay bolts Cabinet|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/700160/fed-up-binay-bolts-cabinet|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-06-23|first = Gil|last = Cabacungan|date = 2015-06-23}}</ref> Two days later, Binay addressed the public from his Coconut Palace offices, branding the current administration as \"manhid at palpak\" (insensitive and bumbling), but did not mention Aquino by name. He also accused the administration of committing sins against him and the people. A photo of Vice President Jejomar Binay has been circulating in social networking sites, wherein he is seen avoiding the muddy ground of an open field by passing through a makeshift bridge while donning his boy scout uniform.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Binay: Aquino government 'palpak'|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/700588/binay-aquino-government-palpak}} A photo of Vice President Jejomar Binay has been circulating in social networking sites, wherein he is seen avoiding the muddy floor of an open field by passing through a makeshift bridge while donning his boy scout uniform.The post has gained mixed reactions from netizens, and has received almost 1,200 shares and nearly a hundred comments as of posting. One online user commented that such an action from one of the country\u2019s highest officials does not make him qualified to hold his post.\n\"And this is the vice president of the Philippines? This guy is not even fit to be a cub scout. So pathetic!\" he said.\nOn the other hand, another user M. J. said, \"OK lang yan. Syempre kahit tayo ayaw din naman nating  maputikan ang sapatos natin\u2026 [Mag pasalamat na lang tayo na pumunta siya dyan, pero hindi ko talaga siya iboboto bilang presidente.\"\n(\"That\u2019s OK. Of course, even us would not want our shoes to get muddy. Let us just be thankful that he went there, but I still would not vote for him to become president.\").</ref>\n\n===Miriam Defensor Santiago===\n{{main|Miriam Defensor Santiago presidential campaign, 2016}}\n\nIn a press conference on July 2, 2014, Senator [[Miriam Defensor Santiago]] ([[People's Reform Party]]) revealed she was suffering from Stage 4 [[lung cancer]] and she might run as president for the third time if it goes into remission. A Magsaysay Awardee, the Nobel Prize of Asia, and the Iron Lady of Asia, she was widely believed to have won the 1992 Philippine Presidential Elections, but lost after hours of blackout during the counting of votes. She once again run for president in 1998, but lost after black propaganda was used against her campaign. She then run for the Senate in the following elections and won with a landslide victory, becoming the most popular female senator and one of the most respected senators in Philippine history with the highest number of laws and bills authored and passed up to this day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/368296/news/nation/senator-miriam-santiago-may-go-for-2016-presidential-bid-if |title=Senator Miriam Santiago may go for 2016 presidential bid if... |work=GMA News |date=2014-07-02 |accessdate=2015-04-26}}</ref>\n\nBy November 2014, Santiago, in a tweet, announced that \"In the 2016 presidential elections, when I am rid of my lung cancer, I intend to claim the presidency I won in [[1992 Philippine presidential election|1992]].\" In a letter to the Senate, Santiago said that more than 90% of the cancer cells have regressed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/11/14/14/miriam-seriously-eyeing-presidency |title=Miriam seriously eyeing presidency |work=ABS-CBNnews.com |date=2014-11-15 |accessdate=2015-04-26}}</ref>\n\nSantiago announced her candidacy for president in the launch of her book ''Stupid is Forever'' on October 13, 2015. She will run under the [[People's Reform Party]], the same party in which she ran under during her 1992 and 1998 presidential campaigns.<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|title = Miriam announces presidential run in 2016|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540496/news/nation/miriam-announces-presidential-run-in-2016|website =GMA News|first=Jessica|last=Bartolome|accessdate = 2015-10-13|date = 2015-10-13}}</ref> Days later, Santiago announced that Senator Bongbong Marcos  would be her vice presidential running mate. Her platform stands on the effective and efficient upholding and implementation of national and state-recognized international laws, enhancement of the agriculture industry with a focus on irrigation and farm-to-market roads, enhancing all seaports and airports in the country, creating at least one major government project in all provinces and all regions in the Philippines, building and highlighting the country's diplomatic affairs in the international level while skyrocketing the country's defense capabilities, and eradicating graft and corruption, which she believes to be the cause of poverty and inefficiency in the country.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|title = Miriam Santiago confirms Bongbong Marcos is her vice president|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/731184/miriam-santiago-confirms-bongbong-marcos-is-her-veep|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-27|date = 2015-10-15|last = Hegina|first = Aries Joseph}}</ref>\n\n===Rodrigo Duterte===\n{{main|Rodrigo Duterte presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Rodrigo Duterte 2013.jpg|thumb|Rodrigo Duterte]]\nThe 2016 presidential campaign of Rodrigo Duterte, the incumbent mayor of [[Davao City]], was announced on November 21, 2015. Duterte had repeatedly refused to run for several months and turned down other presidential and vice-presidential aspirants' offers to be his running mate, including Jejomar Binay, Miriam Defensor-Santiago and Bongbong Marcos.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/duterte-shrugs-off-calls-to-run-for-president/|title=Duterte shrugs off calls to run for president|first=Mary Rose|last=Hogaza|work=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=February 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, Duterte declined [[Miriam Defensor-Santiago]]'s offer to be her running mate and said that instead of being the running mate to Senator Santiago, he wanted [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]] to be Santiago's running mate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/637306/poe-says-no-duterte-tells-santiago-take-gibo-teodoro |title=Poe says no; Duterte tells Santiago: Take Gibo Teodoro |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2014-09-14 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> In March 2015, [[Lakas\u2013CMD]] national president [[Ferdinand Martin Romualdez]] said that his party is preparing for the 2016 elections; [[Danilo Suarez]] also remarked that they are convincing Teodoro to go out of retirement to run anew.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/lakas-cmd-eyeing-gibo-teodoro-for-2016/ |title= Lakas-CMD eyeing 'Gibo' Teodoro for 2016  |first=Ben |last=Rosario |work=[[The Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-03-29 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, Santiago chose [[Bongbong Marcos]] as her running mate in October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miriam Santiago: Bongbong Marcos is my running mate|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109349-miriam-santiago-bongbong-marcos-is-my-running-mate|website=Rappler}}</ref>\n\nDuterte said on a [[Baguio]] federalism forum that he'd run for president \"if only to save the republic.\" Duterte cited the need of about 10 to 15 billion pesos as a campaign war chest that's keeping him from running.<ref name=\"Micua\">{{cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/105388/duterte-to-run-for-president-if-only-to-save-the-republic-but-does-not-have-p10b-in-campaign-money |title=Duterte to run for president 'if only to save the republic' but does not have P10B in campaign money |first=Leonardo V. |last=Micua |work=[[Philippine News Agency]] |publisher=Interaksyon.com |date=February 19, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221211132/http://www.interaksyon.com/article/105388/duterte-to-run-for-president-if-only-to-save-the-republic-but-does-not-have-p10b-in-campaign-money |archivedate=February 21, 2015 }}</ref> Days later, Duterte \"re-entered\" [[PDP-Laban]]; he maintained he never left the party, but had to stand in a local party banner in the 2013 local election to ensure victory.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Esmaquel|first1=Paterno II|title=Duterte 're-enters' PDP-Laban amid 2016 prospects|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/84620-rodrigo-duterte-pdp-laban|accessdate=2015-06-01|work=Rappler.com|date=2015-02-21}}</ref> PDP-Laban president [[Aquilino Pimentel III]] later said that Duterte is among his party's options in nominating for the presidency, noting that the party's position on [[federalism]] coincides with Duterte's advocacy.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/441702/news/nation/pimentel-pdp-laban-might-field-davao-mayor-duterte-in-2016-polls |title=Pimentel: PDP-Laban might field Davao Mayor Duterte in 2016 polls |first=Amanda |last=Fernandez |work=GMA News Online |date=February 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, while at a meeting with military officers, Duterte spoke with [[Communist Party of the Philippines]] (CPP) founder [[Jose Maria Sison]]. Duterte said that he told Sison that he would run for president if the CPP's armed wing, the [[New People's Army]], abandons its [[CPP-NPA-NDF rebellion|over-40-year insurgency]], saying \"Armed struggle as a means to achieve change is pass\u00e9e in the modern world we are living in today,\". Duterte disclosed that Sison was asking him his plans for 2016, and told him that he didn't have plans yet.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Duterte to Joma: I'll run if NPA yields arms|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/711403/duterte-to-joma-ill-run-if-npa-yields-arms|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-08-09|first = Allan|last = Nawal|date = 2015-08-09}}</ref>\n\nWhen making hints to the media of his possible intent to run for the presidency he promised to abolish Congress altogether in favor of a parliament, if he ever wins.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://manila.coconuts.co/2015/01/26/duterte-talks-about-what-hell-do-if-hes-elected-president-2016 |title=Duterte talks about what he'll do if he's elected president in 2016 |newspaper=Coconuts Manila |date=26 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/duterte-eyes-abolition-congress-000000572.html |title=Duterte eyes abolition of Congress |newspaper=Yahoo News Philippines |date=26 January 2015 |first=Ben |last=Serrano}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.philstar.com/nation/2015/01/26/1416721/duterte-eyes-abolition-congress-if-elected-president-2016 |title=Duterte eyes abolition of Congress if elected president in 2016 |newspaper=The Philippine Star |first=Ben |last=Serrano |date=26 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Grace Poe===\n{{main|Grace Poe presidential campaign, 2016}}\n\n[[Grace Poe]]'s surprising first-place finish in the [[2013 Philippine Senate election|2013 Senate election]] as an independent made her a likely contender for the presidency but she dismissed any plans of running in April 2014, saying she was not considering \"anything higher at this point.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/590668/grace-poe-says-shes-not-ready-for-2016-palace-run |title=Grace Poe says she's not ready for 2016 Palace run|first=TJ|last=Burgonio|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=April 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn President Aquino's state visit to Canada in May 2015, the president disclosed that he had met with Poe prior to the trip, although he didn't say on what the meeting was for.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/484522/news/nation/pnoy-confirms-talking-politics-with-poe-but-is-mum-on-details |title=PNoy confirms talking politics with Poe but is mum on details  |first=Andrei |last=Medina |work=GMA News Online |date=May 9, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-17}}</ref> A couple of days later, Poe confirmed that she did meet with Aquino. Poe said that \"We discussed his intention to choose a candidate who, first and foremost, has the trust of the nation, and, secondly, has the potential to win in the election, in order to sustain the reforms especially against corruption and the pro-poor programs of the government.\" Poe expects more meetings with Aquino in June.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/110344/poe-pnoy-offered-no-position-yet-more-talks-seen-this-june |title=Poe: PNoy offered no position yet, more talks seen this June |first=Ernie |last=Reyes |work=Interaksyon.com |date=May 11, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518095936/http://www.interaksyon.com/article/110344/poe-pnoy-offered-no-position-yet-more-talks-seen-this-june |archivedate=May 18, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn June 2, UNA interim president [[Toby Tiangco]], responding to calls for Jejomar Binay to \"come clean\" on his corruption allegations, said in a press conference that Poe is not qualified to run either for president or vice president after citing her certificate of candidacy in the 2013 Senate election which stated that she is a resident for six years and six months; adding three years for the 2016 election, nine years and six months or six months short mandated by the constitution.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Grace Poe lacks residency, not qualified to run for president or VP \u2013 solon|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/695676/grace-poe-lacks-residency-not-qualified-to-run-as-president-or-vp-solon|website = Philippine Daily Inquirer|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = Marc|last = Cayabyab|date = 2015-06-02}}</ref> Two days later, before a Senate session, Poe said that she wrote \"six years and six months\" because it was in April 2006 that her home in the United States was sold. Poe, who had been a resident of the United States for 13 years, returned to the Philippines after her father [[Fernando Poe, Jr.]] died in December 2004. She said that she had proof that she had been living in the Philippines since February 2005. She said, that despite being a congressman for Navotas, Tiangco lives elsewhere, and that her decision on whether to run in 2016 is \"50%\" sure. Poe also observed that the attacks from UNA only began after she signed the Senate Blue Ribbon subcommittee report recommending plunder and graft cases against Binay.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Grace Poe: I'm qualified|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/696058/grace-poe-im-qualified|website = Philippine Daily Inquirer|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = |last = |date = 2015-06-04}}</ref>\n\nOn September 16, at a gathering at the [[University of the Philippines Diliman]] in [[Quezon City]], Poe announced her intention to seek the presidency, saying that \"No one person or group has a monopoly on a straight path advocacy\" of President Aquino, a shot against Aquino's party's nominee Roxas, who is advocating for continuation of the \"Daang Matuwid\" (straight path) advocacy of Aquino; while also hitting the Administration programs. This resulted in the Palace to question their Daang Matuwid advocacy are contrary to their speeches.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Poe in 2016  | url = http://www.mb.com.ph/poe-in-2016/|website = [[Manila Bulletin]]|accessdate = 2015-09-17|first = Hannah|last = Torregoza|date = 2015-09-16}}</ref>\n\nOn December 1, the COMELEC's second division had formally disqualified Poe from running as president in the 2016 elections and cancelled her filed Certificate of Candidacy for not failing to meet with citizenship and residency requirements. The division, was voted 3\u20130, in favor of the petition filed by Atty. Estrella Elamparo to disqualify Poe. The decision stated that Poe had failed to comply with the 10-year residency requiremement, mandatory for a presidential candidate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/546387/news/nation/comelec-division-disqualifies-poe-from-2016-presidential-race|title=Comelec division disqualifies Poe from 2016 presidential race|publisher=GMA News Online|date=1 December 2015|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2016, the Supreme Court determined that Poe is a natural-born Filipino and she returned to the Philippines from the U.S. in 2004, therefore she meets the 10-year residency requirement to run in the presidential election. On April 9, 2016, the Supreme Court declared their ruling as final and executory and she is qualified to become president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/778501/no-more-roadblocks-sc-paves-way-for-grace-poe-run|title=No more roadblocks: SC paves way for Grace Poe run|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|last=Torres-Tupas|first=Tetch|date=April 9, 2016|accessdate=April 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Mar Roxas===\n{{main|Mar Roxas presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Benigno_S._Aquino_III_greets_Corazon_Malanyaon_(cropped_2).jpg|175px|thumb|Mar Roxas]]\nSenate President [[Franklin Drilon]], when describing the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]]'s plans for Interior Secretary [[Mar Roxas]]' in 2016, told the media in January 2013 that \"so far as the LP is concerned, [and] in so far as I am concerned, we believe that he is best qualified for 2016.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/292590/news/nation/drilon-mar-roxas-is-lp-s-bet-in-2016-presidential-polls |title=Drilon: Mar Roxas is LP's bet in 2016 presidential polls |work=GMA News Online |date=January 13, 2013}}</ref> Two years later, Drilon told [[DZIQ]] AM radio that Roxas had expressed his interest internally within the party.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/686291/surprise-roxas-tells-lp-he-will-run-in-2016 |title=Surprise: Roxas tells LP he will run in 2016 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |first1=Leila B. |last1=Salaverria |first2=Ni\u00f1a P. |last2=Calleja |date=April 18, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-18}}</ref> Several Liberal Party stalwarts had by then expressed that Roxas should declare his intentions at that time,<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/489246/news/nation/drilon-tells-mar-roxas-declare-plan-to-run-for-president|title = Drilon tells Mar Roxas: Declare plan to run for President|last = Legaspi|first = Amita O.|date = 2015-05-18|work = GMA News Online|access-date = 2015-05-20|via = }}</ref>  with some such as Budget Secretary [[Florencio Abad]] suggesting that Roxas may slide down to run for the vice presidency again.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/691932/roxas-may-slide-down-for-poe-says-lp|title = Roxas may slide down for Poe, says LP|last = Esguerra|first = Christian V.|date = 2015-05-17|work = INQUIRER.net|access-date = 2015-05-20|via = }}</ref>\n\nAquino had a series of meetings between Roxas, Grace Poe and [[Francis Escudero]] from prior to Aquino's state visit to Canada in May, until days before his final [[State of the Nation Address (Philippines)|State of the Nation Address]] in July, including a July dinner with all three of them at the Bahay Pangarap, Aquino's official residence at the [[Malaca\u00f1ang Palace]] complex. While Roxas was seen as Aquino's choice to succeed him, another question was who would be Roxas' running mate, as Poe had earlier said that she'd rather run with Escudero as her running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Aquino hosts make-or-break dinner meeting|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/705436/dinner-meeting-among-aquino-poe-roxas-escudero-ongoing|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-08-01|first = |last = |date = 2015-07-16}}</ref>\n\nOn July 31, 2015, at an event dubbed as \"A Gathering of Friends\", Roxas formally accepted the Liberal Party's nomination after he was officially endorsed by President [[Benigno Aquino III]] in the presence of their political allies at the [[Club Filipino]], [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], where Roxas had announced his decision to withdraw from the 2010 presidential election and give way to Aquino's presidential bid. Aquino also announced his candidacy there on September 9, 2009.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/531033/news/nation/emotional-roxas-accepts-pnoy-endorsement|title = Emotional Roxas accepts PNoy endorsement |work = [[GMA News]]|date= July 31, 2015|accessdate = 2015-07-31}}</ref>\n\n==Candidates for Vice President==\n\n===Alan Peter Cayetano===\n[[File:Senator_Alan_Peter_S._Cayetano_(cropped).jpg|175px|thumb|Alan Peter Cayetano]]\nIn a March 2013 interview on ''[[Mornings @ ANC]]'', [[Alan Peter Cayetano]] said \"I want to be president of this country.  I think I can do something great for God and his people.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://anc.yahoo.com/news/senator-alan-cayetano-on-2016-polls--i-don%E2%80%99t-want-to-run--i-want-to-win-060709390.html|title=Senator Alan Cayetano on 2016 polls: 'I want to be president'|work=ANC - Yahoo|date=2014-03-05|accessdate=2014-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140308155238/http://anc.yahoo.com/news/senator-alan-cayetano-on-2016-polls--i-don%E2%80%99t-want-to-run--i-want-to-win-060709390.html|archive-date=2014-03-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> By March 2014, he formed a team to prepare for the campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/51787-cayetano-eyes-2016-presidency |title=Cayetano eyes 2016 presidency, forms team |first=Natashya |last=Gutierrez |work=Rappler |date=2014-03-03 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> By October 2014, Cayetano said \"With the present ratings, who would run?\" after a Pulse Asia poll suggests that he is doing poorly. Cayetano clarified though that is not withdrawing from the race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/10/25/1384106/cayetano-undecided-2016-presidential-bid |title= Cayetano undecided on 2016 presidential bid |first=Marvin |last=Sy |work=[[The Philippine Star]] |date=2014-10-25 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref>\n\nA month later, Cayetano said that he is not in a rush to make a decision for the 2016 election, after fellow Nacionalista Senator Trillanes revealed that Cayetano was being considered by their party to run; Cayetano pointed out that it seems that it is Binay who is in a hurry to become president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/390235/news/nation/cayetano-on-2016-polls-hindi-ako-atat |title= Cayetano on 2016 polls: 'Hindi ako atat' |first=Trisha |last=Macas |work=GMA News Online |date=2014-11-28 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> In March 2015, Cayetano said that \"If I do run, I'll run for President and not for Vice President,\" removing him from the vice presidential candidate discussion.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/27/cayetano-won-t-settle-for-2nd-best-in-2016-election/ |title=Cayetano won't settle for 2nd best in 2016 election |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[The New Standard (newspaper)|The New Standard]] |date=2015-03-27 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref>\n\nOn September 16, Cayetano told reporters that he is giving up his plans to run for the presidency in 2016, but hasn't closed his doors for a vice presidential campaign, preferring either to be the running mate of [[Mar Roxas]] or [[Rodrigo Duterte]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Cayetano gives up on presidential bid in 2016|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/722329/cayetano-gives-up-on-presidential-bid-in-2016|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-09-20|first = Yolanda|last = Sotelo|date = 2015-09-16}}</ref>\n\nSenator [[Alan Peter Cayetano]], announced that he will seek candidacy for running as vice president. Cayetano, who he is the member of [[Nacionalista Party]], did not mention his presidential running-mate as NP will meet in a few days, for their decision.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Cayetano to run for VP |url = http://www.philstar.com/election-2016/latest-news/2015/09/29/1505238/cayetano-run-vp |first=Patricia Lourdes |last=Viray |accessdate = 2015-09-29|website = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-09-19}}</ref>\n\n===Francis (Chiz) Escudero===\n[[File:Chiz.jpg|175px|thumb|Francis Escudero]]\nIn a Rappler interview published in April 2012, Senator [[Francis Escudero]] said that \"Let me be honest, candid, yet factual about it. I would be very interested in seeking a higher office in 2016 for the simple reason that I\u2019m halfway through my last term.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/4118--very-interested-in-2016-race|title=Chiz 'very interested' in 2016 race|first=Carmela|last=Fonbuena|work=Rappler.com|date=April 20, 2012}}</ref> In November 2014, Escudero said that he was still unsure of his plans for 2016, and that he would decide on the issue about a year before the election.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Escudero more certain about 2015 'walk' than 2016 run|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/651689/escudero-more-certain-about-2015-walk-than-2016-run|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2014-11-14|last = Ager|first = Maila}}</ref> By May 2015, Escudero admitted that he had discussed with Poe on their possible tandem for the election. Escudero has not yet decided on whether to run for a higher post or not, although Poe said that they would not run against each other.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/93123-francis-escudero-2016-plans |title=Escudero on 2016: Poe and I haven't decided |first=Ayee |last=Macaraig |work=Rappler.com |date=May 14, 2014 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref>\n\nOn September 17, a day after Poe announced her candidacy for the presidency, at the [[Club Filipino]] in [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], Escudero announced his vice presidential bid, becoming Poe's running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = It's official: Grace Poe, Chiz Escudero to run together in 2016|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/722778/its-official-grace-poe-chiz-escudero-to-run-together-in-2016 |first=Maila |last=Ager |accessdate = 2015-09-21|website = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-09-17}}</ref>\n\n===Gregorio Honasan===\n[[File:Gregorio Honasan RAM Duterte meeting (cropped).jpg|175px|thumb|Gringo Honasan]]\nSenator Gregorio Honasan denied there were plans for him to be [[Jejomar Binay|Jejomar Binay's]] running mate in September 2015, saying that \"I have not considered it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Honasan denies tandem with Binay in 2016 polls|url = http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/09/22/honasan-denies-tandem-binay-2016-polls-431698|website = [[Sun.Star]] Manila|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-09-22|last = Gita|first = Ruth Abbey}}</ref> By October 5, Honasan said that a tandem with Binay was possible, saying that \"\"I will subordinate myself to the  decision of the party.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Bi-Hon' tandem in 2016 possible, says Honasan|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/728038/bi-hon-tandem-in-2016-possible-says-honasan|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-10-05|last = Ager|first = Maila}}</ref>\n\nOn October 11, Senator Honasan announced that he will be the running mate of Binay.<ref>http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/718076/now-its-honasan-as-possible-binay-running-mate</ref> He filed his candidacy in the COMELEC Office a day later.\n\n===Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.===\n[[File:Bongbong Marcos.jpg|175px|thumb|Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.|right]]\nAsked in a November 2012 interview on radio [[DZBB-AM|DZBB]] if he is going to run for president, [[Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.]] said he is not closing his doors and \"There\u2019s a saying, \u2018Never say never,\u2019 so maybe.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections-2013/16735-marcos-on-2016-never-say-never |title=Marcos on 2016: Never say never|first=Ayee|last=Macaraig|work=Rappler.com|date=November 25, 2012}}</ref> By June 2013, Nacionalista Party president Manny Villar advised his party-mates who were openly talking about their plans for the 2016 election not to talk about it as it was too early.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Villar to Bongbong: Too early for 2016 plans|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2013/06/25/958093/villar-bongbong-too-early-2016-plans|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2013-06-25|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|last = Bacani|first = Louis}}</ref>\n\nHis mother, Ilocos Norte Representative and former First Lady [[Imelda Marcos]] revealed he wants him to run so he can follow the footsteps and continue the legacy of his father, former President [[Ferdinand Marcos]]. She also added that he is fit for the position because \"He has an impressive track record and a good vision for the country.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/11/13/imelda-wants-bongbong-run-president-2016 |title=Imelda wants Bongbong to run for president in 2016|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn another radio interview, this time at [[DZMM]] AM in March 2015, Marcos said that \"we will thoroughly study everything,\" when asked about people clamoring for him to run. He added that the \"default setting\" for him in 2016 is to defend his Senate seat. This means that he will surely participate in the 2016 elections, but unclear on what position.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/23/bongbong-admits-he-s-eyeing-presidential-run/ |title=Bongbong admits he's eyeing presidential run |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[Manila Standard Today]] |date=March 23, 2015 |accessdate=2015-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330011959/http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/23/bongbong-admits-he-s-eyeing-presidential-run |archive-date=March 30, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn late August, Marcos said that he is open on becoming [[Jejomar Binay]]'s running mate, but clarified that he remained undecided on his plans for 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|title =  Bongbong open to running as Binay's VP |url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/08/26/1492434/bongbong-open-running-binays-vp|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|accessdate = 2015-08-26|first = Patricia Lourdes|last = Viray|date = 2015-09-02}}</ref> Marcos, on an interview at ''Headstart'' at the [[ABS-CBN News Channel]], said that \"The discussions I have been having with different groups, with other individuals have really centered on higher office\", pointing out that he would not run for a second term as senator, but would instead be running either for president or vice president.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong Marcos mulls over Palace run|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/716677/bongbong-marcos-mulls-over-palace-run|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-08-27|first = Leila B.|last = Salaverria|date = 2015-08-27}}</ref>\n\nIn a press statement released to the media on October 5, 2015, Marcos said that he declared his vice presidential bid in 2016, under the [[Nacionalista Party]], although he will support for Davao City Mayor [[Rodrigo Duterte]], if he will run for president. He was also eyeing to be the running mate of Vice President Binay.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong Marcos declares bid for vice presidency in 2016 |url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/539599/news/nation/bongbong-marcos-declares-bid-for-vice-presidency-in-2016 | website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-10-06|date = 2015-10-06}}</ref> Few days after, he formally declared his vice presidential bid at the Puerta Real Garden in Intramuros, Manila. The declaration was also attended by Manila Mayor [[Joseph Estrada]] and Senator [[Juan Ponce Enrile]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong formally announces 2016 vice presidential run |url =http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540225/news/nation/bongbong-formally-announces-2016-vice-presidential-run#sthash.pMx07ELQ.dpuf | website = [[GMA News]]|accessdate = 2015-10-11|date = 2015-10-10}}</ref> On October 15, two days after he filed his COC, Presidentiable [[Miriam Defensor-Santiago]] accepted Marcos to be her running mate.\n\nOn February 4, 2016, The Campaign Against the Return of the Marcoses to Malaca\u00f1ang (CARMMA), was launched to oppose the vice presidential candidacy of Marcos. CARMMA was formed by human rights victims and political prisoners during the Martial Law period in the 1970s under the administration of Former President and Bongbong's father [[Ferdinand Marcos]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2016/02/05/ml-victims-start-campaign-against-return-of-marcoses-to-malacanang/|title=ML victims start campaign against return of Marcoses to Malacanang|publisher=MindaNews|date=February 5, 2016|accessdate=February 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Leni Robredo===\n[[File:Leni Robredo (2).jpg|175px|thumb|Leni Robredo]]\nIn August 2015, [[Leni Robredo]], representative from [[Camarines Sur]] and widow of former Interior and Local Government Secretary [[Jesse Robredo]], remarked that plans of her running for public office in 2016 was \"too soon\", and that the only thing that would convince her to run was if \"I'm indispensable\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Leni Robredo on VP race: 'Too soon'|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/101538-leni-robredo-vp-race-too-soon|website = Rappler|accessdate = 2015-08-05|last = Cupin|first = Bea|date = 2015-08-04}}</ref> A week later, Mar Roxas said that he would still have to talk to her, but he recognizes her abilities, and that should be considered.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Roxas: Leni Robredo qualified, should be considered for VP|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/102975-mar-roxas-leni-robredo-2016|website = Rappler|accessdate = 2015-08-27|last = Cupin|first = Bea}}</ref>\n\nBy September, while attending the 101st anniversary of [[North Cotabato]], said that \"Running for the country\u2019s second highest post was never an option\", and that she \"never dreamed of becoming a vice president\". She instead wanted either [[Alan Peter Cayetano]] or [[Vilma Santos]] to run for vice president, instead, and that she would rather defend her seat in the House of Representatives, or run for the Senate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Robredo says she will not run for VP in 2016 |url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/718381/robredo-says-she-will-not-run-for-vp-in-2016|website = INQUIRER.net |accessdate = 2015-09-13 |date=2015-09-01}}</ref>\n\nBefore the regional cluster meeting of Liberal Party, Sen. Franklin Drilon announced that Robredo will be the party's vice presidential candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|title =  Drilon: Leni is Mar's running mate  |url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/09/30/1505576/drilon-leni-mars-running-mate |website = Philstar.com |accessdate = 2015-09-30 |date=2015-10-05}}</ref> On an event held in the [[Club Filipino]] in San Juan, last October 5, 2015, Robredo accepted the offer to be Mar Roxas' running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Leni Robredo joins VP race  |url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/10/05/15/leni-robredo-joins-vp-race |website = [[ABS-CBN News]] |accessdate = 2015-10-05 |date=2015-10-05}}</ref>\n\n===Antonio Trillanes===\n[[File:Sonny Trillanes.jpg|175px|thumb|Antonio Trillanes IV]]In the news program ''[[Bandila]]'''s May 30, 2014 segment where a guest is asked to answer only \"yes\" or \"no,\" Senator [[Antonio Trillanes IV]] was asked if he would run for vice president in 2016 and responded by saying \"Let\u2019s just say yes, I will run. As for what position, I will abide by the Nacionalista Party.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/606869/trillanes-i-will-run-for-a-higher-position-in-2016|title=Trillanes: I will run for a higher position in 2016|first=Maila|last=Ager|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=May 30, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAlmost a year later, Trillanes announced his preference to run as vice president in a weekly forum at the Senate. As with his May 2014 statement, he says that he would submit to the decision of the Nacionalistas, which would meet sometime before the end of April 2015. Amongst the Nacionalista Party's options are fielding its own standard bearer, form a coalition with the Liberals, or adopt an independent candidate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/679993/trillanes-i-will-run-for-vice-president-in-2016#ixzz3UvY5hcSx |title=Trillanes: I will run for vice president in 2016 |first=Maila|last=Ager|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=March 19, 2015 |accessdate=2015-03-21 }}</ref>\n\nBy August 2015, Trillanes bared his plans of running as an independent vice presidential candidate, saying that the Nacionalistas would not endorse a candidate if more than one of them ran for the vice presidency. Trillanes' own group, Magdalo, his backing his vice presidential bid.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Trillanes to run as independent VP in 2016|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/08/19/1489828/trillanes-run-independent-vp-2016|accessdate = 2015-09-20|date = 2015-08-19|publisher = [[The Philippine Star]]|last = Viray|first = Patricia Lourdes}}</ref>\n\n==Withdrawn candidates==\n===For president===\n====Mel Mendoza====\n\nRomel \"Mel\" Carriedo Mendoza ([[Pwersa ng Masang Pilipino]])<ref name=\"Candidates\"/> works as an assistant project officer and secretary general of Kalipunan ng Masang Pilipino (PMP's affiliate).<ref name=\"Candidates\">{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540359/news/nation/tricycle-driver-home-economics-graduate-among-presidential-hopefuls |title =Tricycle driver, home economics graduate among presidential hopefuls|work = GMA News Online |date= 2015-10-12|accessdate = 2015-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/11/08/1519634/pmp-field-erap-presidential-bet |title=PMP to field Erap as presidential bet? |publisher=The Philippine Star |last=Clapano |first=Jose Rodel |date=8 November 2015|accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"BW 1\">{{cite web |url= http://www.bworldonline.com/content.php?section=TopStory&title=poll-body-releases-initial-list-of-candidates&id=121924 |title=Poll body releases initial list of candidates |publisher=BusinessWorld |last=Clapano |first=Jose Rodel |date=8 November 2015 |accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nMendoza later officially withdrew his candidacy on February 1, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aquino|first1=Leslie Ann|title=Comelec: Presidential aspirants down to six|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/comelec-presidential-aspirants-down-to-six/|accessdate=1 February 2016|publisher=Manila Bulletin|date=1 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Roy Se\u00f1eres====\n[[File:Roy Seneres.png|thumb|Roy Se\u00f1eres]]\nOFW Family Club party-list representative [[Roy Se\u00f1eres]] (1947\u20132016) first revealed his plan to run for the Presidency on October 20, 2014, during the launch of his ''Respect our Security of Employment'' (ROSE) movement in [[Butuan]].<ref>{{cite news|url = http://manilastandardtoday.com/2014/10/20/se-eres-bares-presidential-plans/|title = Se\u00f1eres bares presidential plans|work = Manila Standard Today|first = Alvin T.|last = Guanzon|date = 2014-10-20|accessdate = 2015-09-27}}</ref>\nHe reiterated his plan to run for president in the 2016 presidential election a year later during a briefing at the House of Representatives.<ref name=seneres-2015bid>{{cite news|url = http://rp1.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/10/08/15/seneres-declares-presidential-bid|title = Se\u00f1eres declares presidential bid|work = ABS-CBN News|first = RG|last = Cruz|date = 2015-10-08|accessdate = 2015-10-08|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151018205138/http://rp1.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/10/08/15/seneres-declares-presidential-bid|archivedate = 2015-10-18}}</ref> He planned to run under the [[Partido ng Manggagawa at Magsasaka]] party ticket and field a vice-presidential candidate and a 12-man senatorial slate.<ref name=seneres-2015bid /> He formally launched his presidential bid on October 11, 2015 at the [[Liwasang Bonifacio]] in Manila.<ref name=seneres-2015bid2>{{cite news|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/10/07/1508032/duterte-launch-presidential-bid-paoay|title = Duterte to launch presidential bid in Paoay?\n|work = The Philippine Star|first =Lalaine|last = Jimenea|date = 2015-10-07|accessdate = 2015-10-08}}</ref>\n     \nSe\u00f1eres' bid was a subject of jokes in both social media and with his fellow congressmen who said that Se\u00f1eres was not ready and that he had no chance of winning the election.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pagtakbong president ni Se\u00f1eres, sentro ng biruan (Seneres' presidential bid. a center of jokes |url=http://www.abante.com.ph/news/nat/35840/pagtakbong-president-ni-se-eres-sentro-ng-biruan.html |website=Abante |accessdate=October 9, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151010015930/http://www.abante.com.ph/news/nat/35840/pagtakbong-president-ni-se-eres-sentro-ng-biruan.html |archivedate=October 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn November 22, 2015, he launched the National Headquarters of the [[Partido ng Manggagawa at Magsasaka]] for his presidential campaign in [[Las Pi\u00f1as]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Post on Facebook|url=https://www.facebook.com/seneres2016/photos/a.130872340607643.1073741828.123027141392163/141043779590499/?type=3&theaterhttps://www.facebook.com/seneres2016/photos/a.130872340607643.1073741828.123027141392163/141043779590499/?type=3&theater}}</ref>\n\nSince declared candidate [[Rodrigo Duterte]] of [[PDP-Laban]] faced possible legal problems with his own candidacy, Se\u00f1eres originally opened the possibility that he would allow Rodrigo Duterte as his substitute candidate if Duterte would abide by three conditions, especially being a pro-life advocate.<ref name=\"Archangel\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/545866/news/nation/seneres-open-to-allowing-duterte-as-substitute-candidate|title=Se\u00f1eres open to allowing Duterte as substitute candidate|publisher=GMA News Online|last=Archangel|first=Xianne|date=25 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> However, Se\u00f1eres later refused to substitute and slammed Duterte's decision to pursue the presidency, remarking that Duterte should support and endorse him instead.<ref name=\"Seneres not giving way to Duterte\">{{cite web|title=Seneres not giving way to Duterte|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/11/26/1526039/seneres-not-giving-way-duterte|website=Inquirer|accessdate=November 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCiting his health conditions due to his long-standing diabetes, Se\u00f1eres officially decided to withdraw in the presidential race on February 5, 2016,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/761927/roy-seneres-withdraws-from-presidential-race|title=Roy Se\u00f1eres withdraws from presidential race|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=February 5, 2016|accessdate=February 5, 2016}}</ref> three days before his death.\n\n==Disallowed candidacy==\n\n===For president===\n\n====Augusto Syjuco====\nFormer [[Technical Education and Skills Development Authority]] (TESDA) director-general and [[Iloilo]] representative Augusto \"Boboy\" Syjuco, Jr. announced his presidential bid on October 11, 2015, a day before the filing of the Certificate of Candidacy at the COMELEC offices.He is one of the active oppositionist.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540294/news/nation/ex-tesda-chief-syjuco-to-run-for-president |title =  PEx-TESDA chief Syjuco to run for president |work = GMA News Online|date= 2015-10-11|accessdate = 2015-10-11|first=Xianne|last=Arcangel}}</ref>\n\nHis certificate of candidacy was later cancelled by the COMELEC on December 3 declaring him as a nuisance candidate.<ref>[http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/12/11/1531420/ex-tesda-chief-declared-nuisance-presidential-bet Ex-TESDA chief declared nuisance presidential bet &ndash; ''PhilStar''.]</ref>\n\n====Rizalito David====\n{{main|Rizalito David presidential campaign, 2016}}\nSocio-political analyst [[Rizalito David]] ([[Ang Kapatiran Party]]) formally filed his certificate of candidacy for president on October 12, 2015. He is running under the [[Ang Kapatiran]] Party, which has participated in national elections since 2007.<ref name=david>{{cite web|title = Poe's accuser Rizalito David files COC for president|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540389/news/nation/poe-s-accuser-rizalito-david-files-coc-for-president|website =GMA News|accessdate = 2015-10-12|date = 2015-10-12}}</ref>\n\nCOMELEC declared David a nuisance candidate on December 9 and cancelled his certificate of candidacy.<ref>[http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/746263/comelec-declares-rizalito-david-nuisance-candidate Comelec declares Rizalito David nuisance candidate &ndash; ''Inquirer''.]</ref>\n\nA defeated senatorial candidate in the 2013 midterm elections, David gained prominence recently when he filed a disqualification case against Senator [[Grace Poe]] (also a presidential aspirant) on the grounds of her citizenship.<ref name=david/>\n\n==Candidate selection==\n\n=== Lakas\u2013CMD ===\n[[Lakas\u2013CMD]] has indicated that it would likely nominate Senator [[Bong Revilla]] for president, but is also considering 2010 presidential candidate [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]], who had retired from politics.\n\nRepresentative Danilo Suarez's May 2015 meeting with Vice President Binay in [[Negros Oriental]] suggested an alliance between Lakas and the United Nationalist Alliance. Suarez said that \"We're polarizing towards the UNA. Number one, our chairman emeritus, the former president [[Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo]]... We're very grateful to the vice president to be the only, the highest elected official who is sympathetic to her.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = As Duterte says no to VP run in 2016, UNA may link up with Arroyo's Lakas|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/491998/news/nation/as-duterte-says-no-to-vp-run-in-2016-una-may-link-up-with-arroyo-s-lakas|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-23|website = GMA News Online|last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n===Nacionalista Party===\nOn an April 2015 cruise from Manila to Japan, the Nacionalista Party were supposed to decide on their plans for 2016. However, they were not able to form a consensus on what to do.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title = NP fails to reach consensus on 2016 poll plans|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/689202/np-fails-to-reach-consensus-on-2016-poll-plans|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-05-30|first = Maila|last = Ager}}</ref> In May, [[Cynthia Villar]] said that they are considering adopting Grace Poe as their candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Nacionalista Party open to adopt Poe as 2016 candidate|url = http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/05/19/np-open-adopt-poe-2016-candidate-408274|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-19|website = Sun.Star Manila|last = Gita|first = Ruth Abbey|first2 = John Carlo|last2 = Cahinhinan}}</ref>\n\nWith multiple members angling for the vice presidency, Cynthia Villar said that the party wouldn't impose stand to whom to support for the presidency if two or more members would run for the vice presidency.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/102891-nacionalista-senators-vice-president |title=Marcos, Cayetano, Trillanes for VP? NP to declare 'free zone' |work=Rappler.com |date=2015-08-17 |accessdate=2015-09-02}}</ref> By September, she said that if [[Rodrigo Duterte]] decides to run for the presidency, the Nacionalistas might support him.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/09/01/np-support-duterte-if-he-runs-president-2016-427804 |title=NP to support Duterte if he runs for president in 2016 |first=Ruth Abbey |last=Gita |work=[[Sun.Star]] Manila |date=2015-09-01 |accessdate=2015-09-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Nationalist People's Coalition ===\nIn June 2015, Senator [[Tito Sotto]] of the [[Nationalist People's Coalition]] (NPC), of which no party member had indicated a presidential or vice presidential run, said that while his party had not yet determined its candidates, it favors the tandem of Grace Poe, and former party member Francis Escudero, citing their closeness to the party, and the fact that they had \"no baggage.\" Sotto echoed the earlier statement of NPC president [[Giorgidi Aggabao]]. Discussions with the NPC had earlier suggested supporting the candidacies of Jejomar Binay or [[Panfilo Lacson]], but Sotto said the Poe\u2013Escudero tandem was more attractive.<ref>{{Cite web|title = NPC may field Poe-Escudero team|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/698303/npc-may-field-poe-escudero-team|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-06-14|first = Leila B.|last = Salaverria|date = 2015-06-14}}</ref>\n\nLater that month, Aggabao said that \"Should it happen that the two parties support different candidates, no coalition has been fractured\" as the NPC and the Liberals have no \"formal coalition\" agreement.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/96346-npc-may-split-from-aquino-s-rainbow-coalition-in-2016|title = NPC may split from Aquino's rainbow coalition in 2016|last = Fonbuena|first = Rappler.com|date = 2015-06-14|work = |access-date = 2015-06-17|via = }}</ref> By July, Sotto had said that he had no doubt that Poe would run for president, with Escudero as her running mate. He added that the NPC would meet after Aquino's final State of the Nation Address later that month, and many of its members, including him, are just waiting for Poe to publicize her decision.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Poe to run for President|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/706769/poe-to-run-for-president|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-07-22|first = Gil|last = Cabacungan|date = 2015-07-22}}</ref>\n\nBy August, Aggabao said if Poe decided that she won't run, the party is inclined to support [[Mar Roxas]], \"no question about it.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/710546/npc-to-support-roxas-if-poe-wont-run-for-president|title = NPC to support Roxas if Poe won't run for President|last = Yap|first = DJ|date = 2015-08-05|work = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|access-date = 2015-08-05|via = }}</ref> At the end of the month, the NPC met Poe and Escudero together, their third meeting, after meeting up with Roxas a few weeks earlier.<ref name=\"Grace Poe NPC\">{{cite news |url=http://cnnphilippines.com/news/2015/08/27/NPC-grace-poe-meeting-2016-elections.html |title=NPC meets Poe, Escudero for third time |last=Nicolas |first=Fiona |date=2015-08-27 |work=[[CNN Philippines]] |access-date=2015-08-27}}</ref>\n\n===United Nationalist Alliance===\nIn September 2014, Vice President [[Jejomar Binay]] announced after a meeting at the Century Park Hotel that the [[United Nationalist Alliance]] (UNA), an electoral alliance of the PMP and PDP-Laban, will transform into a full-fledged political party which shall serve as his official vehicle for the 2016 election. The new party shall carry the UNA name and acronym, and sought the approval of the Commission on Elections.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/70021-binay-una-political-party-2016 |title=Binay turns UNA into political party for 2016 |first=Bea |last=Cupin |date=September 24, 2014 |work=Rappler |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> In March 2015, the commission approved UNA's accreditation, allowing it serve as Binay's party for 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/03/27/1437958/comelec-approves-una-party-accreditation |title= Comelec approves UNA party accreditation  |first=Shiela |last=Crisostomo |date=March 27, 2015 |work=[[The Philippine Star]] |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> A May 2015 meeting at Quezon between Binay and Representative Danilo Suarez had indicated a possible alliance between UNA and [[Lakas\u2013CMD]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn July 1, 2015, UNA was launched at the [[Makati Coliseum]], with Binay describing the Aquino administration as \"lazy\", noting the failures of the government in the [[Manila Metro Rail Transit System]] and in the [[Mamasapano clash]], and presented his platform of government. Joseph Estrada was notably absent during the launch.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Main opposition party UNA launched|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/07/02/1472361/main-opposition-party-una-launched|accessdate = 2015-07-02|date = 2015-07-02|publisher = [[The Philippine Star]]|first = Helen|last = Flores}}</ref>\n\n==Declined candidacy==\n\n===For president===\nThese are the people who have personally ruled out the idea of running for either president or vice president.\n\n====Benigno Aquino III====\n[[File:\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e17\u0e27\u0e34\u0e20\u0e32\u0e04\u0e35\u0e23\u0e30\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e07\u0e19\u0e32\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e10\u0e21\u0e19\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35 \u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e18\u0e32\u0e19\u0e32\u0e18\u0e34\u0e1a\u0e14\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e18\u0e32 - Flickr - Abhisit Vejjajiva CROP.jpg|thumb|upright|Benigno Aquino III]]\nIn October 2013, Aquino ruled out a 2016 reelection campaign, even if the presidential term limit is lifted.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/329779/news/nation/pnoy-no-plans-to-extend-term-after-2016 |title=PNoy: No plans to extend term after 2016 |work=GMA News Online |date=2013-10-03 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\nBy May 2014, a [[Facebook]] page calling support for one more term for Aquino was launched, despite the constitutional prohibition for presidential re-election; Presidential Spokesman [[Edwin Lacierda]] said that Aquino \"listens to the voice of his bosses\" (by bosses, meaning the people).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/92745/1-more-term--pnoy-listens-to-the-voice-of-his-bosses---palace |title=1 MORE TERM? PNoy 'listens to the voice of his bosses' - Palace |first=Dexter |last=San Pedro |work=InterAksyon.com |date=2014-08-06 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> On an August 13, 2014 [[TV5 (Philippines)|TV5]] interview by [[Far Eastern University Institute of Law]] Dean [[Mel Sta. Maria]], Aquino confirmed that he is open to the possibility of running again as president in 2016 if a [[Constitutional reform in the Philippines#Aquino Administration|constitutional amendment]] lifting the presidential term limit, amongst other things, is successful.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/93241/video-news5-exclusive--president-aquino-says-he-is-open-to-cha-cha-2nd-term-and-a-weaker-sc |title=VIDEO, NEWS5 EXCLUSIVE President Aquino says he is open to Cha-Cha, 2nd term, and a weaker SC |work=Interaksyon.com |date=2014-08-13 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>  The Liberals openly admitted that Aquino is still their preferred candidate in the election, with Roxas only their second choice.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/374882/news/nation/lps-admit-pnoy-s-their-best-bet-in-2016-mar-only-second-best |title=LPs admit PNoy's their best bet in 2016; Mar, only second best |work=GMA News Online |date=2014-08-14 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref> Binay, for his part, said that he is \"ready\" to face anyone in the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manilatimes.net/binay-vs-pnoy-2016-looms-cha-cha-passes/119310/ |title=Binay vs PNoy in 2016 looms if Cha-cha passes |first=Rhaydz |last=Garcia |work=[[The Manila Times]] |date=2014-08-15 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref>\n\nSeveral months later, Aquino explicitly ruled out a presidential campaign for him in 2016, instead urging voters to \"discern properly\" in voting.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stasiareport.com/the-big-story/asia-report/philippines/story/philippine-president-aquino-rules-out-seeking-second-ter |title=Philippine President Aquino rules out seeking second term |work=[[The Straits Times]] |date=2014-10-28 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\n====Kris Aquino====\nOn April 2, 2013, [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lingayen-Dagupan|Lingayen-Dagupan]] archbishop emeritus [[Oscar Cruz]] has asked presidential sister and actress [[Kris Aquino]]'s camp to clarify reports of her plans on running for the vice presidency because he heard of her political plans from \"credible sources within the administration.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/383725/archbishop-wants-to-know-if-rumor-is-true-kris-aquino-to-run-for-vp |title=Archbishop wants to know if rumor is true: Kris Aquino to run for VP |first=Philip C. |last=Tubeza |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |date=2013-04-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> Presidential spokesperson [[Edwin Lacierda]] denied rumors of her vice presidential candidacy and alluded to Cruz as a \"rumormonger\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/384435/palace-tells-bishop-leave-kris-aquino-alone-rumormonger |title=Palace tells bishop: Leave Kris Aquino alone, 'rumormonger' |first=Michael Lim |last=Ubac |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |date=2013-04-04 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n\nIn a March 2014 edition of her talk show ''[[Aquino & Abunda Tonight]]'', she said the possibility of her candidacy has \"never been discussed\" and added that \"it\u2019s (the election) not yet my time.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2014/03/05/1297355/kris-aquino-denies-shell-run-vice-president-2016 |title=Kris Aquino denies she'll run for Vice President in 2016 |first=Chuck |last=Smith |work=[[Philippine Star]] |date=2014-03-05 |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref>\n\n====JV Ejercito====\nIn May 2014, Senator [[JV Ejercito]] ruled out becoming the running mate of Vice President Binay and said that running for a higher post in the next elections is \"farthest\" from his mind.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/22/14/jv-rules-out-running-binays-vice-cites-same-skin-color |title=JV rules out running as Binay's vice, cites same skin color |first=Willard |last=Cheng |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=2014-05-22 |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref> A year later, with the emergence of [[Grace Poe]] as a possible presidential candidate, Ejercito said that \"I\u2019m in a difficult situation also because both [Poe and Binay] are very close to me.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = JV Ejercito torn between Binay, Poe|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/692392/jv-ejercito-torn-between-binay-poe|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = Christine O.|last = Avenda\u00f1o|date = 2015-05-20}}</ref>\n\n====Jinggoy Estrada====\n[[File:Jinggoy Estrada.jpg|thumb|upright|Jinggoy Estrada]]In an oath-taking ceremony of [[Pwersa ng Masang Pilipino]] members in November 2012, [[Jinggoy Estrada]] compared himself to his father, former president and Manila mayor Joseph Estrada. He said his father describes him as a copycat, saying he also became [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]] mayor, senator and even best actor. But after noting that his father's election to the vice presidency, he said \"It\u2019s up to you what will happen next.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/11/30/12/jinggoy-hints-he-might-become-vice-president|title=Jinggoy hints he might become vice-president|first=RG|last=Cruz|work=ABS-CBN News Online\n|date=November 30, 2012}}</ref>\n\nDespite being implicated in the PDAF scam, he believes critics cannot rule him out as a possible vice presidential candidate and still has the machinery and support to run a campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/53457-jinggoy-support-machinery-2016-bid|title=Jinggoy: I still have support, machinery for 2016|first=Ayee|last=Macaraig|work=Rappler|date=March 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Joseph Estrada====\n[[File:JosephEstradajf1486.JPG|thumb|upright|Joseph Estrada|left]]\nIn February 2014, [[Joseph Estrada]] said that he has already served as president and that his post as [[Mayor of Manila]] will be his \"last hurrah.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/focus/01/10/14/erap-says-he-wont-run-president-again|title=Erap says he won't run for president again|first=Zyann|last=Ambrosio|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=February 5, 2014}}</ref> Almost a year later, Estrada said that he would run if both [[Jejomar Binay]] and [[Grace Poe]] won't run against the administration candidate. If either or both persons run, he said \"I will just be a spectator should VP Binay and Grace run against each other in the 2016 presidential elections.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/erap-may-seek-presidency-000000776.html |title=Erap may seek presidency if\u2026 |first=Jose Rodel |last=Clapano |work=[[Philippine Star]] |publisher=Yahoo! News Philippines |date=January 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, speculations arose that he might replace his son, Senator Jinggoy Estrada, as Binay's running mate due to the former's involvement in the [[PDAF scam]] but he quickly dismissed the rumor, saying he will retire from politics in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/05/27/1327779/erap-dispels-rumors-2016-vp-bid |title=Erap dispels rumors on 2016 VP bid |first=Jose Rodel |last=Calpano |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=2014-05-27 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>  A year later, in a ''[[24 Oras]]'' interview, he said that he is keeping his options open.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/489910/news/nation/erap-not-closing-door-on-possible-third-shot-at-the-presidency |title=Erap not closing door on possible third shot at the presidency |work=GMA News Online |date=May 20, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> Estrada, after Binay proposed a Binay\u2013Estrada tandem in June 2015, Estrada said that he has no interest in running for vice president, and intends to defend the Manila mayoralty.<ref name=\"Clapano\"/>\n\nAfter being conspicuously absent at the launching of UNA, Estrada clarified that he is not a member of UNA, and is instead the head of his own PMP party, which is not in coalition with UNA. However, he said that he will run for president if Binay won't be able to run.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/07/02/1472362/erap-run-if-binay-backs-out|title = Erap to run if Binay backs out|last = |first = |date = 2015-07-02|work = [[The Philippine Star]]|access-date = 2015-07-31|via = }}</ref> By October 2015, Estrada said that he'd run for president if both Binay and Grace Poe were disqualified, to \"preserve democracy in the country\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Erap to run for president if Poe, Binay disqualified|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109137-erap-run-president-if-poe-binay-disqualified|website = Rappler|publisher = Rappler.com|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-10-13|first = Buena|last = Bernal}}</ref>\n\n====Richard J. Gordon====\n[[File:RJGred1.JPG|thumb|upright|Dick Gordon|left]]\n[[Richard J. Gordon]] launched a presidential bid in 2010 for his own party of [[Bagumbayan-VNP]]. Gordon also launched a senatorial bid in 2013 but lost by a close margin to [[Gringo Honasan]] for the final Senate seat. Having a clean and strong track record, Gordon was a potential candidate for 2016. Gordon is a former mayor of [[Olongapo City]], former chairman of the [[Subic Bay Metropolitan Authority]], former secretary of the Department of Tourism and currently serves as chairman of the [[Philippine Red Cross]] after 45 years of volunteering.\n\n====Manny Pacquiao====\n[[File:Manny Pacquiao in Siliman.jpg|thumb|upright|Manny Pacquiao]]\nCongressman from Sarangani [[Manny Pacquiao]] said on [[DZBB-AM|DZBB]] radio during the press conference of his 2011 fight against [[Juan Manuel Marquez]] in Mexico that \"Come 2016 I am going to run (for) vice president... No more boxing at that time.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Manny Pacquiao eyes vice presidency in 2016 polls|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/231937/news/nation/manny-pacquiao-eyes-vice-presidency-in-2016-polls|website = GMA News Online|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2011-09-09}}</ref> but later backtracked when he said \"No, it\u2019s not possible yet. I\u2019m not old enough\" because he will only be 37 years old during the elections \u2013 3 years short of the constitutional age requirement of 40.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/56549/pacquiao-admits-too-young-to-be-vp|title = Pacquiao admits too young to be VP|work = [[Agence France-Presse]]|date = September 10, 2011|publisher = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]}}</ref>\n\nJejomar Binay has later said that Pacquiao is one of the people UNA is eyeing for their senatorial slate.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/52417-binay-pacquiao-senator-2016|title = Binay: Pacquiao our Senate bet for 2016|last = Macaraig|first = Ayee|date = 2014-03-07|work = Rappler.com|access-date = 2015-06-07|via = }}</ref>\n\n====Panfilo Lacson====\n[[File:Sen. Panfilo M. Lacson.jpg|thumb|upright|Panfilo Lacson|left]]\nInterior and Local Government Secretary [[Mar Roxas]] acknowledged that [[Panfilo Lacson]] is qualified to run in for president, but there have been no talks on the latter joining the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]]. Despite of this, he said in February 2014 that he is \"color blind\" to politics and would rather focus on rehabilitating areas hit by [[Typhoon Yolanda]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/12/16/13/mar-ping-qualified-run-president-2016 race|title=Mar: Ping qualified to run in 2016|first=Karen|last=Davila|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=December 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/02/15/1290725/ping-2016-presl-poll-not-mind-too-busy-yolanda|title=Ping: 2016 pres'l poll not in mind, too busy with 'Yolanda'|first=Alexis|last=Romero|work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=February 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAfter resigning as presidential assistant for recovery in February 2015, Lacson, in a press conference at the Diamond Hotel in [[Manila]], told reporters that he is \"not planning, but contemplating\" about running for the presidency. Aside from another presidential campaign, Lacson is considering a return to the Senate, while ruling out local politics.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/83403-ping-lacson-2016-plans |title=Lacson for president in 2016? 'I'm thinking about it' |first=Angela |last=Casauay |work=[[Rappler]]|date=February 9, 2015 |accessdate=2015-02-10}}</ref> In April 2015, Lacson confirmed that he has the intention in running for president, although his final decision would depend on many factors, which he didn't elaborate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/04/11/1442582/lacson-eyeing-presidency-2016 |title= Lacson eyeing presidency in 2016 |first=Cecille |last=Suerte Felipe |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=April 11, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-12}}</ref> On a press conference at [[Baguio]] a couple of weeks later, Lacson announced his intention to be an independent candidate for president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/baguio/local-news/2015/04/24/lacson-i-may-run-president-404201 |title=Lacson: 'I may run as president'|first=Giovani Joy |last=Fontanilla |work=[[Sun.Star]] Baguio|date=April 24, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-25}}</ref> A month later, Lacson said that he will announce his decision to run for president after the next survey is released.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/05/21/ping-to-wait-for-survey-before-deciding/ |title=Ping to wait for survey before deciding |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[The New Standard (newspaper)|The New Standard]] |date=May 21, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, he will no longer seek to run for president, but instead he now focused on his possible return to the senate in the coming elections.\n\n====Francis Pangilinan====\nIn May 2014, then newly appointed Presidential Adviser on Food Security and Agricultural Modernization [[Francis Pangilinan]] said that \"I'm not interested in the presidency, and I\u2019m not interested in the elections at this time.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Pangilinan not interested in 2016 elections\u2026'at this time'|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/600106/pangilinan-not-interested-in-2016-electionsat-this-time|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-06-17|first = |last = |date = 2014-05-06}}</ref> By December 2014, a \"Poe-Kiko\", a pun on the Tagalog phrase for \"my vagina\", tandem of [[Grace Poe]] and Pangilinan was making rounds; Pangilinan describe it as \"a joke\" on the Christmas party of the National Irrigation Administration. and wished Poe \"lives up to everybody's expectations.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Poe-Kiko' team just a joke, says Pangilinan - Manila Standard Today|url = http://manilastandardtoday.com/2014/12/15/-poe-kiko-team-just-a-joke-says-pangilinan/|accessdate = 2015-06-17|date = 2014-12-15|website = [[The New Standard (Philippine newspaper)|The New Standard]]}}</ref>\n\nBy late August 2015, Pangilinan said in a budget briefing at the House of Representatives that he would announce his announce for 2016 \"after the ghost month\" of the Chinese calendar ends in September 12, with the Liberal Party looking to see him to lead the \"powerhouse\" senatorial ticket.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Kiko Pangilinan to announce 2016 plan after 'ghost month'|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/534271/news/nation/kiko-pangilinan-to-announce-2016-plan-after-ghost-month|accessdate = 2015-08-27|date = 2015-08-25|website = GMA News Online}}</ref>\n\n====Manny Pangilinan====\n[[File:Manuel_Pangilinan_2012.jpg|thumb|upright|Manny Pangilinan]]\nBy late 2010, [[Manny Pangilinan]], chairman of utility companies [[PLDT]] and [[Meralco]]. and of [[TV5 (Philippines)|TV5]], is claimed as a \"dark horse\" by political analysts.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/focus/10/06/13/mvp-dark-horse-2016-polls |title=MVP a dark horse in 2016 polls? |first=Kathlyn |last= dela Cruz |work=[[ABS-CBN]] |date=2013-10-06 |accessdate=2013-10-06}}</ref> The businessman later commented on the rumors that he would seek an elective position, saying \"there is no political blood that runs through my veins. I believe I can serve our people better some other way.\" He also said his decision was \"final\" amid encouragement from various sectors that he would make a great president, given his \"technocratic skills.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lectura|first=Lenie|title=Exclusive: MVP: Not running in 2016|url=http://businessmirror.com.ph/index.php/en/news/top-news/20912-exclusive-mvp-not-running-in-2016|publisher=BusinessMirror}}</ref>\n\n====Bong Revilla====\n[[File:Ramon Bong Revilla.JPG|thumb|left|upright|Bong Revilla]]\nIn January 2013, then House Minority Leader Danilo Suarez, [[Lakas-CMD]] vice-chairman, said that their party is likely considering [[Bong Revilla]] to be their candidate.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/349679/lakas-cmd-grooming-bong-revilla-for-2016-presidential-race|title=Lakas-CMD grooming Bong Revilla for 2016 presidential race|first=Karen|last=Boncocan|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=January 30, 2013}}</ref> Revilla later revealed that he is open to running for president and his involvement in the [[Priority Development Assistance Fund scam]] (PDAF scam) would not affect his political ambition.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/revilla-eyes-2016-presidency/ |title=Revilla eyes 2016 presidency |first=Mario |last=Casayuran |work=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-05-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150531015702/http://www.mb.com.ph/revilla-eyes-2016-presidency/ |archivedate=2015-05-31 }}</ref>\n\nAfters being jailed at the Philippine National Police custodial center in Quezon City due to the PDAF scam, Revilla in May 2015 said that he is still open to running in 2016, as no law prohibits incarcerated people from running. When pushed further, Revilla said \"\"No comment,\" as he may not be able to \"get free: because of it.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/490774/news/nation/bong-revilla-open-to-running-for-higher-office-in-2016-polls |title=Bong Revilla open to running for higher office in 2016 polls |first=Elizabeth |last=Marcelo |work=GMA News Online |date=2015-05-23 }}</ref>\n\nWhile still in detention for his involvement in the PDAF scam, Revilla told reporters that his presidential ambition caused his detention, and that he was a \"at a loss\" on what to do once the filing of candidacies started, On his plans for the presidency, he said that \" I\u2019m not in a hurry. I\u2019m still young\", and that he wanted to clear his name first before running.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Revilla says presidential ambition caused his detention for plunder|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/726535/revilla-says-presidential-ambition-caused-his-detention-for-plunder|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|publisher = |date = 2015-09-30|first = Marc Jayson|last = Cayabyab}}</ref>\n\n====Vilma Santos====\n[[File:Vilma Santos DOH Medical Assistance for Indigent Program MOA signing (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Vilma Santos]]\nVice President Binay's visit to [[Batangas]] in February 2014 fueled speculation that provincial governor [[Vilma Santos]] might be his running mate. In a later interview, he finally admitted to considering her as his vice-presidential candidate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/03/02/14/binay-considering-vilma-running-mate-2016 |title=Binay considering Vilma as running mate in 2016 |work=ABS-CBNnews.com |date=2014-03-02 |accessdate=2015-03-15}}</ref> However, her husband, Senator [[Ralph Recto]], said in March 2014 that she is not planning to run for a higher position and might retire from politics instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/581945/vilma-santos-has-no-plans-for-2016-might-retire-from-politics-sen-recto< |title=Vilma has no plans for 2016, might retire from politics\u2014Sen. Recto |first=Matikas |last=Santos |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2015-03-03 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2015, after Duterte suggested that she could be his running mate, Santos herself dismissed reports that she is running for a higher position, and echoing her husbands earlier statements, may opt to return to showbiz instead after her term ends.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/503086/news/regions/batangas-gov-vilma-santos-denies-rumors-she-will-run-in-2016-elections|title = Batangas Gov. Vilma Santos denies rumors she will run in 2016 elections|last = |first = |date = 2015-06-12|work = GMA News Online|access-date = 2015-06-17|via = }}</ref> Two months later, Santos said that if she'd run for public office in 2016, is that it would be for congresswoman from Batangas, and that she isn't running for vice president.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Vilma insists she won't run for VP|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/08/04/15/vilma-insists-she-wont-run-vp|accessdate = 2015-08-04|first = Jay|last = Ruiz|website = abs-cbnnews.com|date = 2015-08-04}}</ref>\n\n====Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.====\n[[File:Gates Teodoro Press Conference 090601 cropped3.jpg|thumb|upright|Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]]\nIn September 2014, Davao City mayor Rodrigo Duterte said that, instead of being the running mate to Senator Santiago, he wanted [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]] to be his running mate.<ref name=\"INQUIRER.net\">{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/637306/poe-says-no-duterte-tells-santiago-take-gibo-teodoro |title=Poe says no; Duterte tells Santiago: Take Gibo Teodoro |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2014-09-14 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> In March 2015, [[Lakas\u2013CMD]] national president [[Ferdinand Martin Romualdez]] said that his party is preparing for the 2016 elections; [[Danilo Suarez]] also remarked that they are convincing Teodoro to go out of retirement to run anew.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/lakas-cmd-eyeing-gibo-teodoro-for-2016/ |title= Lakas-CMD eyeing 'Gibo' Teodoro for 2016  |first=Ben |last=Rosario |work=[[The Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-03-29 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, Santiago chose [[Bongbong Marcos]] as her running mate in October 2015, the month after Alan Cayetano announced his bid for the vice presidency as Duterte's running mate.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|title=Miriam Santiago: Bongbong Marcos is my running mate|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109349-miriam-santiago-bongbong-marcos-is-my-running-mate|website=Rappler}}</ref>\n\n====Manny Villar====\n[[File:Manny Villar T'nalak Festival 2009.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Manny Villar]]\nHis wife, Senator [[Cynthia Villar]], did not rule the possibility of him running for president again, saying in March 2014 \"You know, for [[Manny Villar|Manny]], presidency is destiny for him after 2010. He said if it\u2019s meant for you, then it will come. If not, then it won\u2019t come.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/589202/villar-may-run-again-for-president-says-wife|title = Villar may run again for president, says wife|work = Inquirer.net|date = March 26, 2014|first = Maila|last = Ager|access-date = 2015-06-01}}</ref> Later, that year, when [[Jejomar Binay]] identified the former senator as a potential running mate, Cynthia said that \"Villar is not running for vice president. Never.\"<ref name=\"Rappler.com\"/>\n\nIn May 2015, Trillanes pushed for Villar to run anew,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Trillanes pushing NP leader Villar for another presidential run|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/483498/news/nation/trillanes-pushing-np-leader-villar-for-another-presidential-run|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-07|website = GMA News Online|last = Sisante|first = Johanna Camille}}</ref> while his Villar's wife Cynthia said that the Nacionalistas failed to agree on their plans for 2016 during their Manila-Japan cruise, citing that it's too early to decide on plans for 2016 as the cause.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title = NP fails to reach consensus on 2016 poll plans|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/689202/np-fails-to-reach-consensus-on-2016-poll-plans|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-05-30|first = Maila|last = Ager}}</ref> By October, Villar's son [[Mark Villar|Mark]], also the representative from Las Pi\u00f1as, said that \"My father's definitely not running next election\", adding that the elder Villar was enjoying his time as a businessman.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Manny Villar won't run in 2016, son says|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/10/09/15/manny-villar-wont-run-2016-son-says|website = ABS-CBN News|accessdate = 2015-10-15|last = Cruz|first = RG|date = 2015-10-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{2016 Philippine elections}}\n\n[[Category:Candidates in the 2016 Philippine presidential election| ]]\n", "text_old": "This is a list of '''candidates in the [[2016 Philippine presidential election|Philippine presidential and vice presidential elections of 2016]]''' {{As of|2016|05|02|df=US|lc=y}}.\n\n==Candidates for President==\nThese are people who submitted candidacies, and were allowed to run by the Commission on Elections and to be included in ballots.\n\n===Jejomar Binay===\n{{main|Jejomar Binay presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Jejomar Binay.jpg|upright|thumb|Jejomar Binay]]\nWhen he was questioned by the media at the [[Coconut Palace]] in September 2011, Vice President [[Jejomar Binay]] ([[United Nationalist Alliance|UNA]]) confirmed his plans to run for president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/13/11/binay-run-president-2016|title=Binayaran wants to run for president in 2016|first=Atom|last=Araullo|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=September 13, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nBy May 2014, Binay began his search for a running mate. As his potential running mate Senator [[Jinggoy Estrada]] in jail due to his implication in the [[Priority Development Assistance Fund scam|PDAF scam]],<ref name=\"Macaraig\">{{cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/53457-jinggoy-support-machinery-2016-bid|title = Jinggoy: I still have support, machinery for 2016|first = Ayee|last = Macaraig|work = Rappler|date = March 20, 2014}}</ref> Binay's offers were declined by [[JV Ejercito]],<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/22/14/jv-rules-out-running-binays-vice-cites-same-skin-color|title = JV rules out running as Binay's vice, cites same skin color|first = Willard|last = Cheng|work = [[Philippine Star]]|date = 2014-05-22|accessdate = 2014-06-08}}</ref> [[Manny Villar]] (via wife [[Cynthia Villar]]),<ref name=\"Rappler.com\">{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/76220-manny-villar-2016-plans|title = Manny Villar for VP? 'Never,' says wife|last = |first = |date = 2014-11-06|work = Rappler.com|access-date = 2015-06-07|via = }}</ref> [[Vilma Santos]] (via husband [[Ralph Recto]]),<ref>{{cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/581945/vilma-santos-has-no-plans-for-2016-might-retire-from-politics-sen-recto<|title = Vilma has no plans for 2016, might retire from politics\u2014Sen. Recto|first = Matikas|last = Santos|work = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-03-03|accessdate = 2015-05-13}}</ref> [[Mar Roxas]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = Roxas not even thinking of being VP Binay's running mate in 2016|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/467754/news/nation/roxas-not-even-thinking-of-being-vp-binay-s-running-mate-in-2016|accessdate = 2015-06-22|date = 2015-04-10|website = GMA News Online}}</ref> [[Grace Poe]],<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/490374/news/nation/grace-poe-doesn-t-see-herself-as-vp-binay-s-running-mate|title = Grace Poe doesn't see herself as VP Binay's running mate|first = Johanna Camille|last = Sisante|work = GMA News Online|date = May 20, 2015|accessdate = 2015-05-24}}</ref> [[Rodrigo Duterte]]<ref name=\"duterte may23\">{{cite news|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/23/15/duterte-i-wont-run-national-post-2016|title = Duterte: I won't run for national post in 2016|work = ABS-CBNnews.com|date = 2015-05-23|accessdate = 2015-05-23}}</ref> and [[Joseph Estrada]].<ref name=\"Clapano\">{{Cite web|title = Erap not interested in running for VP|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/06/07/1463063/erap-not-interested-running-vp|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2015-06-07|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|publisher = |last = Clapano|first = Jose Rodel}}</ref> Binay's daughter [[Abigail Binay|Abigail]], also the Representative from Makati, said that Binay would accept anyone as his running mate except for [[Antonio Trillanes]], and that she prefers [[Grace Poe]], however Sen. [[Bongbong Marcos]] was the most preferred by UNA officials to be his running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Binay's running mate 'anyone but Trillanes'|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/05/19/1456467/binays-running-mate-anyone-trillanes|accessdate = 2015-06-22|date = 2015-05-19|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|first = Patricia Lourdes|publisher = |last = Viray}}</ref> In a 2015 Independence Day (June 12) speech in [[Iloilo]], President Aquino said that he could only offer Binay the conduct of a clean and honest election, but not an outright endorsement.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Mar gets Noy's praise but still no endorsement|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/06/13/1465293/mar-gets-noys-praise-still-no-endorsement|accessdate = 2015-06-13|date = 2015-06-13|website = [[The Philippine Star]]}}</ref>\n\nA few days later, on June 22, Binay resigned from the Aquino cabinet, both as presidential adviser on [[Overseas Filipino Workers]]' concerns and as chairman of the Housing and Urban Development Coordinating Council, but did not say why.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Fed up, Binay bolts Cabinet|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/700160/fed-up-binay-bolts-cabinet|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-06-23|first = Gil|last = Cabacungan|date = 2015-06-23}}</ref> Two days later, Binay addressed the public from his Coconut Palace offices, branding the current administration as \"manhid at palpak\" (insensitive and bumbling), but did not mention Aquino by name. He also accused the administration of committing sins against him and the people. A photo of Vice President Jejomar Binay has been circulating in social networking sites, wherein he is seen avoiding the muddy ground of an open field by passing through a makeshift bridge while donning his boy scout uniform.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Binay: Aquino government 'palpak'|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/700588/binay-aquino-government-palpak}} A photo of Vice President Jejomar Binay has been circulating in social networking sites, wherein he is seen avoiding the muddy floor of an open field by passing through a makeshift bridge while donning his boy scout uniform.The post has gained mixed reactions from netizens, and has received almost 1,200 shares and nearly a hundred comments as of posting. One online user commented that such an action from one of the country\u2019s highest officials does not make him qualified to hold his post.\n\"And this is the vice president of the Philippines? This guy is not even fit to be a cub scout. So pathetic!\" he said.\nOn the other hand, another user M. J. said, \"OK lang yan. Syempre kahit tayo ayaw din naman nating  maputikan ang sapatos natin\u2026 [Mag pasalamat na lang tayo na pumunta siya dyan, pero hindi ko talaga siya iboboto bilang presidente.\"\n(\"That\u2019s OK. Of course, even us would not want our shoes to get muddy. Let us just be thankful that he went there, but I still would not vote for him to become president.\").</ref>\n\n===Miriam Defensor Santiago===\n{{main|Miriam Defensor Santiago presidential campaign, 2016}}\n\nIn a press conference on July 2, 2014, Senator [[Miriam Defensor Santiago]] ([[People's Reform Party]]) revealed she was suffering from Stage 4 [[lung cancer]] and she might run as president for the third time if it goes into remission. A Magsaysay Awardee, the Nobel Prize of Asia, and the Iron Lady of Asia, she was widely believed to have won the 1992 Philippine Presidential Elections, but lost after hours of blackout during the counting of votes. She once again run for president in 1998, but lost after black propaganda was used against her campaign. She then run for the Senate in the following elections and won with a landslide victory, becoming the most popular female senator and one of the most respected senators in Philippine history with the highest number of laws and bills authored and passed up to this day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/368296/news/nation/senator-miriam-santiago-may-go-for-2016-presidential-bid-if |title=Senator Miriam Santiago may go for 2016 presidential bid if... |work=GMA News |date=2014-07-02 |accessdate=2015-04-26}}</ref>\n\nBy November 2014, Santiago, in a tweet, announced that \"In the 2016 presidential elections, when I am rid of my lung cancer, I intend to claim the presidency I won in [[1992 Philippine presidential election|1992]].\" In a letter to the Senate, Santiago said that more than 90% of the cancer cells have regressed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/11/14/14/miriam-seriously-eyeing-presidency |title=Miriam seriously eyeing presidency |work=ABS-CBNnews.com |date=2014-11-15 |accessdate=2015-04-26}}</ref>\n\nSantiago announced her candidacy for president in the launch of her book ''Stupid is Forever'' on October 13, 2015. She will run under the [[People's Reform Party]], the same party in which she ran under during her 1992 and 1998 presidential campaigns.<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|title = Miriam announces presidential run in 2016|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540496/news/nation/miriam-announces-presidential-run-in-2016|website =GMA News|first=Jessica|last=Bartolome|accessdate = 2015-10-13|date = 2015-10-13}}</ref> Days later, Santiago announced that Senator Bongbong Marcos  would be her vice presidential running mate. Her platform stands on the effective and efficient upholding and implementation of national and state-recognized international laws, enhancement of the agriculture industry with a focus on irrigation and farm-to-market roads, enhancing all seaports and airports in the country, creating at least one major government project in all provinces and all regions in the Philippines, building and highlighting the country's diplomatic affairs in the international level while skyrocketing the country's defense capabilities, and eradicating graft and corruption, which she believes to be the cause of poverty and inefficiency in the country.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|title = Miriam Santiago confirms Bongbong Marcos is her vice president|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/731184/miriam-santiago-confirms-bongbong-marcos-is-her-veep|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-27|date = 2015-10-15|last = Hegina|first = Aries Joseph}}</ref>\n\n===Rodrigo Duterte===\n{{main|Rodrigo Duterte presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Rodrigo Duterte 2013.jpg|thumb|Rodrigo Duterte]]\nThe 2016 presidential campaign of Rodrigo Duterte, the incumbent mayor of [[Davao City]], was announced on November 21, 2015. Duterte had repeatedly refused to run for several months and turned down other presidential and vice-presidential aspirants' offers to be his running mate, including Jejomar Binay, Miriam Defensor-Santiago and Bongbong Marcos.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/duterte-shrugs-off-calls-to-run-for-president/|title=Duterte shrugs off calls to run for president|first=Mary Rose|last=Hogaza|work=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=February 5, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, Duterte declined [[Miriam Defensor-Santiago]]'s offer to be her running mate and said that instead of being the running mate to Senator Santiago, he wanted [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]] to be Santiago's running mate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/637306/poe-says-no-duterte-tells-santiago-take-gibo-teodoro |title=Poe says no; Duterte tells Santiago: Take Gibo Teodoro |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2014-09-14 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> In March 2015, [[Lakas\u2013CMD]] national president [[Ferdinand Martin Romualdez]] said that his party is preparing for the 2016 elections; [[Danilo Suarez]] also remarked that they are convincing Teodoro to go out of retirement to run anew.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/lakas-cmd-eyeing-gibo-teodoro-for-2016/ |title= Lakas-CMD eyeing 'Gibo' Teodoro for 2016  |first=Ben |last=Rosario |work=[[The Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-03-29 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, Santiago chose [[Bongbong Marcos]] as her running mate in October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miriam Santiago: Bongbong Marcos is my running mate|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109349-miriam-santiago-bongbong-marcos-is-my-running-mate|website=Rappler}}</ref>\n\nDuterte said on a [[Baguio]] federalism forum that he'd run for president \"if only to save the republic.\" Duterte cited the need of about 10 to 15 billion pesos as a campaign war chest that's keeping him from running.<ref name=\"Micua\">{{cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/105388/duterte-to-run-for-president-if-only-to-save-the-republic-but-does-not-have-p10b-in-campaign-money |title=Duterte to run for president 'if only to save the republic' but does not have P10B in campaign money |first=Leonardo V. |last=Micua |work=[[Philippine News Agency]] |publisher=Interaksyon.com |date=February 19, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221211132/http://www.interaksyon.com/article/105388/duterte-to-run-for-president-if-only-to-save-the-republic-but-does-not-have-p10b-in-campaign-money |archivedate=February 21, 2015 }}</ref> Days later, Duterte \"re-entered\" [[PDP-Laban]]; he maintained he never left the party, but had to stand in a local party banner in the 2013 local election to ensure victory.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Esmaquel|first1=Paterno II|title=Duterte 're-enters' PDP-Laban amid 2016 prospects|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/84620-rodrigo-duterte-pdp-laban|accessdate=2015-06-01|work=Rappler.com|date=2015-02-21}}</ref> PDP-Laban president [[Aquilino Pimentel III]] later said that Duterte is among his party's options in nominating for the presidency, noting that the party's position on [[federalism]] coincides with Duterte's advocacy.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/441702/news/nation/pimentel-pdp-laban-might-field-davao-mayor-duterte-in-2016-polls |title=Pimentel: PDP-Laban might field Davao Mayor Duterte in 2016 polls |first=Amanda |last=Fernandez |work=GMA News Online |date=February 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, while at a meeting with military officers, Duterte spoke with [[Communist Party of the Philippines]] (CPP) founder [[Jose Maria Sison]]. Duterte said that he told Sison that he would run for president if the CPP's armed wing, the [[New People's Army]], abandons its [[CPP-NPA-NDF rebellion|over-40-year insurgency]], saying \"Armed struggle as a means to achieve change is pass\u00e9e in the modern world we are living in today,\". Duterte disclosed that Sison was asking him his plans for 2016, and told him that he didn't have plans yet.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Duterte to Joma: I'll run if NPA yields arms|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/711403/duterte-to-joma-ill-run-if-npa-yields-arms|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-08-09|first = Allan|last = Nawal|date = 2015-08-09}}</ref>\n\nWhen making hints to the media of his possible intent to run for the presidency he promised to abolish Congress altogether in favor of a parliament, if he ever wins.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://manila.coconuts.co/2015/01/26/duterte-talks-about-what-hell-do-if-hes-elected-president-2016 |title=Duterte talks about what he'll do if he's elected president in 2016 |newspaper=Coconuts Manila |date=26 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/duterte-eyes-abolition-congress-000000572.html |title=Duterte eyes abolition of Congress |newspaper=Yahoo News Philippines |date=26 January 2015 |first=Ben |last=Serrano}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.philstar.com/nation/2015/01/26/1416721/duterte-eyes-abolition-congress-if-elected-president-2016 |title=Duterte eyes abolition of Congress if elected president in 2016 |newspaper=The Philippine Star |first=Ben |last=Serrano |date=26 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Grace Poe===\n{{main|Grace Poe presidential campaign, 2016}}\n\n[[Grace Poe]]'s surprising first-place finish in the [[2013 Philippine Senate election|2013 Senate election]] as an independent made her a likely contender for the presidency but she dismissed any plans of running in April 2014, saying she was not considering \"anything higher at this point.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/590668/grace-poe-says-shes-not-ready-for-2016-palace-run |title=Grace Poe says she's not ready for 2016 Palace run|first=TJ|last=Burgonio|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=April 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn President Aquino's state visit to Canada in May 2015, the president disclosed that he had met with Poe prior to the trip, although he didn't say on what the meeting was for.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/484522/news/nation/pnoy-confirms-talking-politics-with-poe-but-is-mum-on-details |title=PNoy confirms talking politics with Poe but is mum on details  |first=Andrei |last=Medina |work=GMA News Online |date=May 9, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-17}}</ref> A couple of days later, Poe confirmed that she did meet with Aquino. Poe said that \"We discussed his intention to choose a candidate who, first and foremost, has the trust of the nation, and, secondly, has the potential to win in the election, in order to sustain the reforms especially against corruption and the pro-poor programs of the government.\" Poe expects more meetings with Aquino in June.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/110344/poe-pnoy-offered-no-position-yet-more-talks-seen-this-june |title=Poe: PNoy offered no position yet, more talks seen this June |first=Ernie |last=Reyes |work=Interaksyon.com |date=May 11, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518095936/http://www.interaksyon.com/article/110344/poe-pnoy-offered-no-position-yet-more-talks-seen-this-june |archivedate=May 18, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn June 2, UNA interim president [[Toby Tiangco]], responding to calls for Jejomar Binay to \"come clean\" on his corruption allegations, said in a press conference that Poe is not qualified to run either for president or vice president after citing her certificate of candidacy in the 2013 Senate election which stated that she is a resident for six years and six months; adding three years for the 2016 election, nine years and six months or six months short mandated by the constitution.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Grace Poe lacks residency, not qualified to run for president or VP \u2013 solon|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/695676/grace-poe-lacks-residency-not-qualified-to-run-as-president-or-vp-solon|website = Philippine Daily Inquirer|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = Marc|last = Cayabyab|date = 2015-06-02}}</ref> Two days later, before a Senate session, Poe said that she wrote \"six years and six months\" because it was in April 2006 that her home in the United States was sold. Poe, who had been a resident of the United States for 13 years, returned to the Philippines after her father [[Fernando Poe, Jr.]] died in December 2004. She said that she had proof that she had been living in the Philippines since February 2005. She said, that despite being a congressman for Navotas, Tiangco lives elsewhere, and that her decision on whether to run in 2016 is \"50%\" sure. Poe also observed that the attacks from UNA only began after she signed the Senate Blue Ribbon subcommittee report recommending plunder and graft cases against Binay.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Grace Poe: I'm qualified|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/696058/grace-poe-im-qualified|website = Philippine Daily Inquirer|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = |last = |date = 2015-06-04}}</ref>\n\nOn September 16, at a gathering at the [[University of the Philippines Diliman]] in [[Quezon City]], Poe announced her intention to seek the presidency, saying that \"No one person or group has a monopoly on a straight path advocacy\" of President Aquino, a shot against Aquino's party's nominee Roxas, who is advocating for continuation of the \"Daang Matuwid\" (straight path) advocacy of Aquino; while also hitting the Administration programs. This resulted in the Palace to question their Daang Matuwid advocacy are contrary to their speeches.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Poe in 2016  | url = http://www.mb.com.ph/poe-in-2016/|website = [[Manila Bulletin]]|accessdate = 2015-09-17|first = Hannah|last = Torregoza|date = 2015-09-16}}</ref>\n\nOn December 1, the COMELEC's second division had formally disqualified Poe from running as President in the 2016 elections and cancelled her filed Certificate of Candidacy for not failing to meet with citizenship and residency requirements. The division, was voted 3-0, in favor of the petition filed by Atty. Estrella Elamparo to disqualify Poe. The decision stated that Poe had failed to comply with the 10-year residency requiremement, mandatory for a presidential candidate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/546387/news/nation/comelec-division-disqualifies-poe-from-2016-presidential-race|title=Comelec division disqualifies Poe from 2016 presidential race|publisher=GMA News Online|date=1 December 2015|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2016, the Supreme Court determined that Poe is a natural-born Filipino and she returned to the Philippines from the U.S. in 2004, therefore she meets the 10-year residency requirement to run in the presidential election. On April 9, 2016, the Supreme Court declared their ruling as final and executory and she is qualified to become president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/778501/no-more-roadblocks-sc-paves-way-for-grace-poe-run|title=No more roadblocks: SC paves way for Grace Poe run|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|last=Torres-Tupas|first=Tetch|date=April 9, 2016|accessdate=April 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Mar Roxas===\n{{main|Mar Roxas presidential campaign, 2016}}\n[[File:Benigno_S._Aquino_III_greets_Corazon_Malanyaon_(cropped_2).jpg|175px|thumb|Mar Roxas]]\nSenate President [[Franklin Drilon]], when describing the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]]'s plans for Interior Secretary [[Mar Roxas]]' in 2016, told the media in January 2013 that \"so far as the LP is concerned, [and] in so far as I am concerned, we believe that he is best qualified for 2016.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/292590/news/nation/drilon-mar-roxas-is-lp-s-bet-in-2016-presidential-polls |title=Drilon: Mar Roxas is LP's bet in 2016 presidential polls |work=GMA News Online |date=January 13, 2013}}</ref> Two years later, Drilon told [[DZIQ]] AM radio that Roxas had expressed his interest internally within the party.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/686291/surprise-roxas-tells-lp-he-will-run-in-2016 |title=Surprise: Roxas tells LP he will run in 2016 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |first1=Leila B. |last1=Salaverria |first2=Ni\u00f1a P. |last2=Calleja |date=April 18, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-18}}</ref> Several Liberal Party stalwarts had by then expressed that Roxas should declare his intentions at that time,<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/489246/news/nation/drilon-tells-mar-roxas-declare-plan-to-run-for-president|title = Drilon tells Mar Roxas: Declare plan to run for President|last = Legaspi|first = Amita O.|date = 2015-05-18|work = GMA News Online|access-date = 2015-05-20|via = }}</ref>  with some such as Budget Secretary [[Florencio Abad]] suggesting that Roxas may slide down to run for the vice presidency again.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/691932/roxas-may-slide-down-for-poe-says-lp|title = Roxas may slide down for Poe, says LP|last = Esguerra|first = Christian V.|date = 2015-05-17|work = INQUIRER.net|access-date = 2015-05-20|via = }}</ref>\n\nAquino had a series of meetings between Roxas, Grace Poe and [[Francis Escudero]] from prior to Aquino's state visit to Canada in May, until days before his final [[State of the Nation Address (Philippines)|State of the Nation Address]] in July, including a July dinner with all three of them at the Bahay Pangarap, Aquino's official residence at the [[Malaca\u00f1ang Palace]] complex. While Roxas was seen as Aquino's choice to succeed him, another question was who would be Roxas' running mate, as Poe had earlier said that she'd rather run with Escudero as her running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Aquino hosts make-or-break dinner meeting|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/705436/dinner-meeting-among-aquino-poe-roxas-escudero-ongoing|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-08-01|first = |last = |date = 2015-07-16}}</ref>\n\nOn July 31, 2015, at an event dubbed as \"A Gathering of Friends\", Roxas formally accepted the Liberal Party's nomination after he was officially endorsed by President [[Benigno Aquino III]] in the presence of their political allies at the [[Club Filipino]], [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], where Roxas had announced his decision to withdraw from the 2010 presidential election and give way to Aquino's presidential bid. Aquino also announced his candidacy there on September 9, 2009.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/531033/news/nation/emotional-roxas-accepts-pnoy-endorsement|title = Emotional Roxas accepts PNoy endorsement |work = [[GMA News]]|date= July 31, 2015|accessdate = 2015-07-31}}</ref>\n\n==Candidates for Vice President==\n\n===Alan Peter Cayetano===\n[[File:Senator_Alan_Peter_S._Cayetano_(cropped).jpg|175px|thumb|Alan Peter Cayetano]]\nIn a March 2013 interview on ''[[Mornings @ ANC]]'', [[Alan Peter Cayetano]] said \"I want to be president of this country.  I think I can do something great for God and his people.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://anc.yahoo.com/news/senator-alan-cayetano-on-2016-polls--i-don%E2%80%99t-want-to-run--i-want-to-win-060709390.html|title=Senator Alan Cayetano on 2016 polls: 'I want to be president'|work=ANC - Yahoo|date=2014-03-05|accessdate=2014-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140308155238/http://anc.yahoo.com/news/senator-alan-cayetano-on-2016-polls--i-don%E2%80%99t-want-to-run--i-want-to-win-060709390.html|archive-date=2014-03-08|url-status=dead}}</ref> By March 2014, he formed a team to prepare for the campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/51787-cayetano-eyes-2016-presidency |title=Cayetano eyes 2016 presidency, forms team |first=Natashya |last=Gutierrez |work=Rappler |date=2014-03-03 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> By October 2014, Cayetano said \"With the present ratings, who would run?\" after a Pulse Asia poll suggests that he is doing poorly. Cayetano clarified though that is not withdrawing from the race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/10/25/1384106/cayetano-undecided-2016-presidential-bid |title= Cayetano undecided on 2016 presidential bid |first=Marvin |last=Sy |work=[[The Philippine Star]] |date=2014-10-25 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref>\n\nA month later, Cayetano said that he is not in a rush to make a decision for the 2016 election, after fellow Nacionalista Senator Trillanes revealed that Cayetano was being considered by their party to run; Cayetano pointed out that it seems that it is Binay who is in a hurry to become president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/390235/news/nation/cayetano-on-2016-polls-hindi-ako-atat |title= Cayetano on 2016 polls: 'Hindi ako atat' |first=Trisha |last=Macas |work=GMA News Online |date=2014-11-28 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> In March 2015, Cayetano said that \"If I do run, I'll run for President and not for Vice President,\" removing him from the vice presidential candidate discussion.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/27/cayetano-won-t-settle-for-2nd-best-in-2016-election/ |title=Cayetano won't settle for 2nd best in 2016 election |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[The New Standard (newspaper)|The New Standard]] |date=2015-03-27 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref>\n\nOn September 16, Cayetano told reporters that he is giving up his plans to run for the presidency in 2016, but hasn't closed his doors for a vice presidential campaign, preferring either to be the running mate of [[Mar Roxas]] or [[Rodrigo Duterte]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Cayetano gives up on presidential bid in 2016|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/722329/cayetano-gives-up-on-presidential-bid-in-2016|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-09-20|first = Yolanda|last = Sotelo|date = 2015-09-16}}</ref>\n\nSenator [[Alan Peter Cayetano]], announced that he will seek candidacy for running as Vice President. Cayetano, who he is the member of [[Nacionalista Party]], did not mention his Presidential running-mate as NP will meet in a few days, for their decision.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Cayetano to run for VP |url = http://www.philstar.com/election-2016/latest-news/2015/09/29/1505238/cayetano-run-vp |first=Patricia Lourdes |last=Viray |accessdate = 2015-09-29|website = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-09-19}}</ref>\n\n===Francis (Chiz) Escudero===\n[[File:Chiz.jpg|175px|thumb|Francis Escudero]]\nIn a Rappler interview published in April 2012, Senator [[Francis Escudero]] said that \"Let me be honest, candid, yet factual about it. I would be very interested in seeking a higher office in 2016 for the simple reason that I\u2019m halfway through my last term.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/4118--very-interested-in-2016-race|title=Chiz 'very interested' in 2016 race|first=Carmela|last=Fonbuena|work=Rappler.com|date=April 20, 2012}}</ref> In November 2014, Escudero said that he was still unsure of his plans for 2016, and that he would decide on the issue about a year before the election.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Escudero more certain about 2015 'walk' than 2016 run|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/651689/escudero-more-certain-about-2015-walk-than-2016-run|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2014-11-14|last = Ager|first = Maila}}</ref> By May 2015, Escudero admitted that he had discussed with Poe on their possible tandem for the election. Escudero has not yet decided on whether to run for a higher post or not, although Poe said that they would not run against each other.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/93123-francis-escudero-2016-plans |title=Escudero on 2016: Poe and I haven't decided |first=Ayee |last=Macaraig |work=Rappler.com |date=May 14, 2014 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref>\n\nOn September 17, a day after Poe announced her candidacy for the presidency, at the [[Club Filipino]] in [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], Escudero announced his vice presidential bid, becoming Poe's running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = It's official: Grace Poe, Chiz Escudero to run together in 2016|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/722778/its-official-grace-poe-chiz-escudero-to-run-together-in-2016 |first=Maila |last=Ager |accessdate = 2015-09-21|website = INQUIRER.net|date = 2015-09-17}}</ref>\n\n===Gregorio Honasan===\n[[File:Gregorio Honasan RAM Duterte meeting (cropped).jpg|175px|thumb|Gringo Honasan]]\nSenator Gregorio Honasan denied there were plans for him to be [[Jejomar Binay|Jejomar Binay's]] running mate in September 2015, saying that \"I have not considered it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Honasan denies tandem with Binay in 2016 polls|url = http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/09/22/honasan-denies-tandem-binay-2016-polls-431698|website = [[Sun.Star]] Manila|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-09-22|last = Gita|first = Ruth Abbey}}</ref> By October 5, Honasan said that a tandem with Binay was possible, saying that \"\"I will subordinate myself to the  decision of the party.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Bi-Hon' tandem in 2016 possible, says Honasan|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/728038/bi-hon-tandem-in-2016-possible-says-honasan|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-10-05|last = Ager|first = Maila}}</ref>\n\nOn October 11, Senator Honasan announced that he will be the running mate of Binay.<ref>http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/718076/now-its-honasan-as-possible-binay-running-mate</ref> He filed his candidacy in the COMELEC Office a day later.\n\n===Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.===\n[[File:Bongbong Marcos.jpg|175px|thumb|Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.|right]]\nAsked in a November 2012 interview on radio [[DZBB-AM|DZBB]] if he is going to run for president, [[Ferdinand Marcos, Jr.]] said he is not closing his doors and \"There\u2019s a saying, \u2018Never say never,\u2019 so maybe.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections-2013/16735-marcos-on-2016-never-say-never |title=Marcos on 2016: Never say never|first=Ayee|last=Macaraig|work=Rappler.com|date=November 25, 2012}}</ref> By June 2013, Nacionalista Party president Manny Villar advised his party-mates who were openly talking about their plans for the 2016 election not to talk about it as it was too early.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Villar to Bongbong: Too early for 2016 plans|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2013/06/25/958093/villar-bongbong-too-early-2016-plans|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2013-06-25|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|last = Bacani|first = Louis}}</ref>\n\nHis mother, Ilocos Norte Representative and former First Lady [[Imelda Marcos]] revealed he wants him to run so he can follow the footsteps and continue the legacy of his father, former President [[Ferdinand Marcos]]. She also added that he is fit for the position because \"He has an impressive track record and a good vision for the country.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/11/13/imelda-wants-bongbong-run-president-2016 |title=Imelda wants Bongbong to run for president in 2016|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn another radio interview, this time at [[DZMM]] AM in March 2015, Marcos said that \"we will thoroughly study everything,\" when asked about people clamoring for him to run. He added that the \"default setting\" for him in 2016 is to defend his Senate seat. This means that he will surely participate in the 2016 elections, but unclear on what position.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/23/bongbong-admits-he-s-eyeing-presidential-run/ |title=Bongbong admits he's eyeing presidential run |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[Manila Standard Today]] |date=March 23, 2015 |accessdate=2015-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330011959/http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/03/23/bongbong-admits-he-s-eyeing-presidential-run |archive-date=March 30, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn late August, Marcos said that he is open on becoming [[Jejomar Binay]]'s running mate, but clarified that he remained undecided on his plans for 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|title =  Bongbong open to running as Binay's VP |url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/08/26/1492434/bongbong-open-running-binays-vp|website = [[The Philippine Star]]|accessdate = 2015-08-26|first = Patricia Lourdes|last = Viray|date = 2015-09-02}}</ref> Marcos, on an interview at ''Headstart'' at the [[ABS-CBN News Channel]], said that \"The discussions I have been having with different groups, with other individuals have really centered on higher office\", pointing out that he would not run for a second term as senator, but would instead be running either for president or vice president.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong Marcos mulls over Palace run|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/716677/bongbong-marcos-mulls-over-palace-run|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-08-27|first = Leila B.|last = Salaverria|date = 2015-08-27}}</ref>\n\nIn a press statement released to the media on October 5, 2015, Marcos said that he declared his vice presidential bid in 2016, under the [[Nacionalista Party]], although he will support for Davao City Mayor [[Rodrigo Duterte]], if he will run for president. He was also eyeing to be the running mate of Vice President Binay.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong Marcos declares bid for vice presidency in 2016 |url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/539599/news/nation/bongbong-marcos-declares-bid-for-vice-presidency-in-2016 | website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-10-06|date = 2015-10-06}}</ref> Few days after, he formally declared his vice presidential bid at the Puerta Real Garden in Intramuros, Manila. The declaration was also attended by Manila Mayor [[Joseph Estrada]] and Senator [[Juan Ponce Enrile]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Bongbong formally announces 2016 vice presidential run |url =http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540225/news/nation/bongbong-formally-announces-2016-vice-presidential-run#sthash.pMx07ELQ.dpuf | website = [[GMA News]]|accessdate = 2015-10-11|date = 2015-10-10}}</ref> On October 15, two days after he filed his COC, Presidentiable [[Miriam Defensor-Santiago]] accepted Marcos to be her running mate.\n\nOn February 4, 2016, The Campaign Against the Return of the Marcoses to Malaca\u00f1ang (CARMMA), was launched to oppose the vice presidential candidacy of Marcos. CARMMA was formed by human rights victims and political prisoners during the Martial Law period in the 1970s under the administration of Former President and Bongbong's father [[Ferdinand Marcos]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2016/02/05/ml-victims-start-campaign-against-return-of-marcoses-to-malacanang/|title=ML victims start campaign against return of Marcoses to Malacanang|publisher=MindaNews|date=February 5, 2016|accessdate=February 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Leni Robredo===\n[[File:Leni Robredo (2).jpg|175px|thumb|Leni Robredo]]\nIn August 2015, [[Leni Robredo]], representative from [[Camarines Sur]] and widow of former Interior and Local Government Secretary [[Jesse Robredo]], remarked that plans of her running for public office in 2016 was \"too soon\", and that the only thing that would convince her to run was if \"I'm indispensable\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Leni Robredo on VP race: 'Too soon'|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/101538-leni-robredo-vp-race-too-soon|website = Rappler|accessdate = 2015-08-05|last = Cupin|first = Bea|date = 2015-08-04}}</ref> A week later, Mar Roxas said that he would still have to talk to her, but he recognizes her abilities, and that should be considered.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Roxas: Leni Robredo qualified, should be considered for VP|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/102975-mar-roxas-leni-robredo-2016|website = Rappler|accessdate = 2015-08-27|last = Cupin|first = Bea}}</ref>\n\nBy September, while attending the 101st anniversary of [[North Cotabato]], said that \"Running for the country\u2019s second highest post was never an option\", and that she \"never dreamed of becoming a vice president\". She instead wanted either [[Alan Peter Cayetano]] or [[Vilma Santos]] to run for vice president, instead, and that she would rather defend her seat in the House of Representatives, or run for the Senate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Robredo says she will not run for VP in 2016 |url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/718381/robredo-says-she-will-not-run-for-vp-in-2016|website = INQUIRER.net |accessdate = 2015-09-13 |date=2015-09-01}}</ref>\n\nBefore the regional cluster meeting of Liberal Party, Sen. Franklin Drilon announced that Robredo will be the party's vice presidential candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|title =  Drilon: Leni is Mar's running mate  |url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/09/30/1505576/drilon-leni-mars-running-mate |website = Philstar.com |accessdate = 2015-09-30 |date=2015-10-05}}</ref> On an event held in the [[Club Filipino]] in San Juan, last October 5, 2015, Robredo accepted the offer to be Mar Roxas' running mate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Leni Robredo joins VP race  |url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/10/05/15/leni-robredo-joins-vp-race |website = [[ABS-CBN News]] |accessdate = 2015-10-05 |date=2015-10-05}}</ref>\n\n===Antonio Trillanes===\n[[File:Sonny Trillanes.jpg|175px|thumb|Antonio Trillanes IV]]In the news program ''[[Bandila]]'''s May 30, 2014 segment where a guest is asked to answer only \"yes\" or \"no,\" Senator [[Antonio Trillanes IV]] was asked if he would run for vice president in 2016 and responded by saying \"Let\u2019s just say yes, I will run. As for what position, I will abide by the Nacionalista Party.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/606869/trillanes-i-will-run-for-a-higher-position-in-2016|title=Trillanes: I will run for a higher position in 2016|first=Maila|last=Ager|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=May 30, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAlmost a year later, Trillanes announced his preference to run as vice president in a weekly forum at the Senate. As with his May 2014 statement, he says that he would submit to the decision of the Nacionalistas, which would meet sometime before the end of April 2015. Amongst the Nacionalista Party's options are fielding its own standard bearer, form a coalition with the Liberals, or adopt an independent candidate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/679993/trillanes-i-will-run-for-vice-president-in-2016#ixzz3UvY5hcSx |title=Trillanes: I will run for vice president in 2016 |first=Maila|last=Ager|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=March 19, 2015 |accessdate=2015-03-21 }}</ref>\n\nBy August 2015, Trillanes bared his plans of running as an independent vice presidential candidate, saying that the Nacionalistas would not endorse a candidate if more than one of them ran for the vice presidency. Trillanes' own group, Magdalo, his backing his vice presidential bid.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Trillanes to run as independent VP in 2016|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/08/19/1489828/trillanes-run-independent-vp-2016|accessdate = 2015-09-20|date = 2015-08-19|publisher = [[The Philippine Star]]|last = Viray|first = Patricia Lourdes}}</ref>\n\n==Withdrawn candidates==\n===For president===\n====Mel Mendoza====\n\nRomel \"Mel\" Carriedo Mendoza ([[Pwersa ng Masang Pilipino]])<ref name=\"Candidates\"/> works as an assistant project officer and secretary general of Kalipunan ng Masang Pilipino (PMP's affiliate).<ref name=\"Candidates\">{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540359/news/nation/tricycle-driver-home-economics-graduate-among-presidential-hopefuls |title =Tricycle driver, home economics graduate among presidential hopefuls|work = GMA News Online |date= 2015-10-12|accessdate = 2015-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/11/08/1519634/pmp-field-erap-presidential-bet |title=PMP to field Erap as presidential bet? |publisher=The Philippine Star |last=Clapano |first=Jose Rodel |date=8 November 2015|accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"BW 1\">{{cite web |url= http://www.bworldonline.com/content.php?section=TopStory&title=poll-body-releases-initial-list-of-candidates&id=121924 |title=Poll body releases initial list of candidates |publisher=BusinessWorld |last=Clapano |first=Jose Rodel |date=8 November 2015 |accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nMendoza later officially withdrew his candidacy on February 1, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aquino|first1=Leslie Ann|title=Comelec: Presidential aspirants down to six|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/comelec-presidential-aspirants-down-to-six/|accessdate=1 February 2016|publisher=Manila Bulletin|date=1 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Roy Se\u00f1eres====\n[[File:Roy Seneres.png|thumb|Roy Se\u00f1eres]]\nOFW Family Club party-list representative [[Roy Se\u00f1eres]] (1947\u20132016) first revealed his plan to run for the Presidency on October 20, 2014, during the launch of his ''Respect our Security of Employment'' (ROSE) movement in [[Butuan]].<ref>{{cite news|url = http://manilastandardtoday.com/2014/10/20/se-eres-bares-presidential-plans/|title = Se\u00f1eres bares presidential plans|work = Manila Standard Today|first = Alvin T.|last = Guanzon|date = 2014-10-20|accessdate = 2015-09-27}}</ref>\nHe reiterated his plan to run for President in the 2016 presidential election a year later during a briefing at the House of Representatives.<ref name=seneres-2015bid>{{cite news|url = http://rp1.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/10/08/15/seneres-declares-presidential-bid|title = Se\u00f1eres declares presidential bid|work = ABS-CBN News|first = RG|last = Cruz|date = 2015-10-08|accessdate = 2015-10-08|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151018205138/http://rp1.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/10/08/15/seneres-declares-presidential-bid|archivedate = 2015-10-18}}</ref> He planned to run under the [[Partido ng Manggagawa at Magsasaka]] party ticket and field a vice-presidential candidate and a 12-man senatorial slate.<ref name=seneres-2015bid /> He formally launched his presidential bid on October 11, 2015 at the [[Liwasang Bonifacio]] in Manila.<ref name=seneres-2015bid2>{{cite news|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/10/07/1508032/duterte-launch-presidential-bid-paoay|title = Duterte to launch presidential bid in Paoay?\n|work = The Philippine Star|first =Lalaine|last = Jimenea|date = 2015-10-07|accessdate = 2015-10-08}}</ref>\n     \nSe\u00f1eres' bid was a subject of jokes in both social media and with his fellow congressmen who said that Se\u00f1eres was not ready and that he had no chance of winning the election.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pagtakbong president ni Se\u00f1eres, sentro ng biruan (Seneres' presidential bid. a center of jokes |url=http://www.abante.com.ph/news/nat/35840/pagtakbong-president-ni-se-eres-sentro-ng-biruan.html |website=Abante |accessdate=October 9, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151010015930/http://www.abante.com.ph/news/nat/35840/pagtakbong-president-ni-se-eres-sentro-ng-biruan.html |archivedate=October 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn November 22, 2015, he launched the National Headquarters of the [[Partido ng Manggagawa at Magsasaka]] for his presidential campaign in [[Las Pi\u00f1as]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Post on Facebook|url=https://www.facebook.com/seneres2016/photos/a.130872340607643.1073741828.123027141392163/141043779590499/?type=3&theaterhttps://www.facebook.com/seneres2016/photos/a.130872340607643.1073741828.123027141392163/141043779590499/?type=3&theater}}</ref>\n\nSince declared candidate [[Rodrigo Duterte]] of [[PDP-Laban]] faced possible legal problems with his own candidacy, Se\u00f1eres originally opened the possibility that he would allow Rodrigo Duterte as his substitute candidate if Duterte would abide by three conditions, especially being a pro-life advocate.<ref name=\"Archangel\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/545866/news/nation/seneres-open-to-allowing-duterte-as-substitute-candidate|title=Se\u00f1eres open to allowing Duterte as substitute candidate|publisher=GMA News Online|last=Archangel|first=Xianne|date=25 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> However, Se\u00f1eres later refused to substitute and slammed Duterte's decision to pursue the presidency, remarking that Duterte should support and endorse him instead.<ref name=\"Seneres not giving way to Duterte\">{{cite web|title=Seneres not giving way to Duterte|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/11/26/1526039/seneres-not-giving-way-duterte|website=Inquirer|accessdate=November 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCiting his health conditions due to his long-standing diabetes, Se\u00f1eres officially decided to withdraw in the presidential race on February 5, 2016,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/761927/roy-seneres-withdraws-from-presidential-race|title=Roy Se\u00f1eres withdraws from presidential race|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=February 5, 2016|accessdate=February 5, 2016}}</ref> three days before his death.\n\n==Disallowed candidacy==\n\n===For president===\n\n====Augusto Syjuco====\nFormer [[Technical Education and Skills Development Authority]] (TESDA) director-general and [[Iloilo]] representative Augusto \"Boboy\" Syjuco, Jr. announced his presidential bid on October 11, 2015, a day before the filing of the Certificate of Candidacy at the COMELEC offices.He is one of the active oppositionist.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540294/news/nation/ex-tesda-chief-syjuco-to-run-for-president |title =  PEx-TESDA chief Syjuco to run for president |work = GMA News Online|date= 2015-10-11|accessdate = 2015-10-11|first=Xianne|last=Arcangel}}</ref>\n\nHis certificate of candidacy was later cancelled by the COMELEC on December 3 declaring him as a nuisance candidate.<ref>[http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/12/11/1531420/ex-tesda-chief-declared-nuisance-presidential-bet Ex-TESDA chief declared nuisance presidential bet &ndash; ''PhilStar''.]</ref>\n\n====Rizalito David====\n{{main|Rizalito David presidential campaign, 2016}}\nSocio-political analyst [[Rizalito David]] ([[Ang Kapatiran Party]]) formally filed his certificate of candidacy for President on October 12, 2015. He is running under the [[Ang Kapatiran]] Party, which has participated in national elections since 2007.<ref name=david>{{cite web|title = Poe's accuser Rizalito David files COC for president|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/540389/news/nation/poe-s-accuser-rizalito-david-files-coc-for-president|website =GMA News|accessdate = 2015-10-12|date = 2015-10-12}}</ref>\n\nCOMELEC declared David a nuisance candidate on December 9 and cancelled his certificate of candidacy.<ref>[http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/746263/comelec-declares-rizalito-david-nuisance-candidate Comelec declares Rizalito David nuisance candidate &ndash; ''Inquirer''.]</ref>\n\nA defeated senatorial candidate in the 2013 midterm elections, David gained prominence recently when he filed a disqualification case against Senator [[Grace Poe]] (also a presidential aspirant) on the grounds of her citizenship.<ref name=david/>\n\n==Candidate selection==\n\n=== Lakas\u2013CMD ===\n[[Lakas\u2013CMD]] has indicated that it would likely nominate Senator [[Bong Revilla]] for President, but is also considering 2010 presidential candidate [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]], who had retired from politics.\n\nRepresentative Danilo Suarez's May 2015 meeting with Vice President Binay in [[Negros Oriental]] suggested an alliance between Lakas and the United Nationalist Alliance. Suarez said that \"We're polarizing towards the UNA. Number one, our chairman emeritus, the former president [[Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo]]... We're very grateful to the vice president to be the only, the highest elected official who is sympathetic to her.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = As Duterte says no to VP run in 2016, UNA may link up with Arroyo's Lakas|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/491998/news/nation/as-duterte-says-no-to-vp-run-in-2016-una-may-link-up-with-arroyo-s-lakas|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-23|website = GMA News Online|last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n===Nacionalista Party===\nOn an April 2015 cruise from Manila to Japan, the Nacionalista Party were supposed to decide on their plans for 2016. However, they were not able to form a consensus on what to do.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title = NP fails to reach consensus on 2016 poll plans|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/689202/np-fails-to-reach-consensus-on-2016-poll-plans|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-05-30|first = Maila|last = Ager}}</ref> In May, [[Cynthia Villar]] said that they are considering adopting Grace Poe as their candidate.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Nacionalista Party open to adopt Poe as 2016 candidate|url = http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/05/19/np-open-adopt-poe-2016-candidate-408274|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-19|website = Sun.Star Manila|last = Gita|first = Ruth Abbey|first2 = John Carlo|last2 = Cahinhinan}}</ref>\n\nWith multiple members angling for the vice presidency, Cynthia Villar said that the party wouldn't impose stand to whom to support for the presidency if two or more members would run for the vice presidency.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/102891-nacionalista-senators-vice-president |title=Marcos, Cayetano, Trillanes for VP? NP to declare 'free zone' |work=Rappler.com |date=2015-08-17 |accessdate=2015-09-02}}</ref> By September, she said that if [[Rodrigo Duterte]] decides to run for the presidency, the Nacionalistas might support him.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/manila/local-news/2015/09/01/np-support-duterte-if-he-runs-president-2016-427804 |title=NP to support Duterte if he runs for president in 2016 |first=Ruth Abbey |last=Gita |work=[[Sun.Star]] Manila |date=2015-09-01 |accessdate=2015-09-02}}</ref>\n\n=== Nationalist People's Coalition ===\nIn June 2015, Senator [[Tito Sotto]] of the [[Nationalist People's Coalition]] (NPC), of which no party member had indicated a presidential or vice presidential run, said that while his party had not yet determined its candidates, it favors the tandem of Grace Poe, and former party member Francis Escudero, citing their closeness to the party, and the fact that they had \"no baggage.\" Sotto echoed the earlier statement of NPC president [[Giorgidi Aggabao]]. Discussions with the NPC had earlier suggested supporting the candidacies of Jejomar Binay or [[Panfilo Lacson]], but Sotto said the Poe\u2013Escudero tandem was more attractive.<ref>{{Cite web|title = NPC may field Poe-Escudero team|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/698303/npc-may-field-poe-escudero-team|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-06-14|first = Leila B.|last = Salaverria|date = 2015-06-14}}</ref>\n\nLater that month, Aggabao said that \"Should it happen that the two parties support different candidates, no coalition has been fractured\" as the NPC and the Liberals have no \"formal coalition\" agreement.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/96346-npc-may-split-from-aquino-s-rainbow-coalition-in-2016|title = NPC may split from Aquino's rainbow coalition in 2016|last = Fonbuena|first = Rappler.com|date = 2015-06-14|work = |access-date = 2015-06-17|via = }}</ref> By July, Sotto had said that he had no doubt that Poe would run for president, with Escudero as her running mate. He added that the NPC would meet after Aquino's final State of the Nation Address later that month, and many of its members, including him, are just waiting for Poe to publicize her decision.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Poe to run for President|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/706769/poe-to-run-for-president|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-07-22|first = Gil|last = Cabacungan|date = 2015-07-22}}</ref>\n\nBy August, Aggabao said if Poe decided that she won't run, the party is inclined to support [[Mar Roxas]], \"no question about it.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/710546/npc-to-support-roxas-if-poe-wont-run-for-president|title = NPC to support Roxas if Poe won't run for President|last = Yap|first = DJ|date = 2015-08-05|work = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|access-date = 2015-08-05|via = }}</ref> At the end of the month, the NPC met Poe and Escudero together, their third meeting, after meeting up with Roxas a few weeks earlier.<ref name=\"Grace Poe NPC\">{{cite news |url=http://cnnphilippines.com/news/2015/08/27/NPC-grace-poe-meeting-2016-elections.html |title=NPC meets Poe, Escudero for third time |last=Nicolas |first=Fiona |date=2015-08-27 |work=[[CNN Philippines]] |access-date=2015-08-27}}</ref>\n\n===United Nationalist Alliance===\nIn September 2014, Vice President [[Jejomar Binay]] announced after a meeting at the Century Park Hotel that the [[United Nationalist Alliance]] (UNA), an electoral alliance of the PMP and PDP-Laban, will transform into a full-fledged political party which shall serve as his official vehicle for the 2016 election. The new party shall carry the UNA name and acronym, and sought the approval of the Commission on Elections.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/70021-binay-una-political-party-2016 |title=Binay turns UNA into political party for 2016 |first=Bea |last=Cupin |date=September 24, 2014 |work=Rappler |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> In March 2015, the commission approved UNA's accreditation, allowing it serve as Binay's party for 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/03/27/1437958/comelec-approves-una-party-accreditation |title= Comelec approves UNA party accreditation  |first=Shiela |last=Crisostomo |date=March 27, 2015 |work=[[The Philippine Star]] |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> A May 2015 meeting at Quezon between Binay and Representative Danilo Suarez had indicated a possible alliance between UNA and [[Lakas\u2013CMD]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn July 1, 2015, UNA was launched at the [[Makati Coliseum]], with Binay describing the Aquino administration as \"lazy\", noting the failures of the government in the [[Manila Metro Rail Transit System]] and in the [[Mamasapano clash]], and presented his platform of government. Joseph Estrada was notably absent during the launch.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = Main opposition party UNA launched|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/07/02/1472361/main-opposition-party-una-launched|accessdate = 2015-07-02|date = 2015-07-02|publisher = [[The Philippine Star]]|first = Helen|last = Flores}}</ref>\n\n==Declined candidacy==\n\n===For president===\nThese are the people who have personally ruled out the idea of running for either president or vice president.\n\n====Benigno Aquino III====\n[[File:\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e23\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e17\u0e27\u0e34\u0e20\u0e32\u0e04\u0e35\u0e23\u0e30\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u0e07\u0e19\u0e32\u0e22\u0e01\u0e23\u0e31\u0e10\u0e21\u0e19\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35 \u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e18\u0e32\u0e19\u0e32\u0e18\u0e34\u0e1a\u0e14\u0e35\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e18\u0e32 - Flickr - Abhisit Vejjajiva CROP.jpg|thumb|upright|Benigno Aquino III]]\nIn October 2013, Aquino ruled out a 2016 reelection campaign, even if the presidential term limit is lifted.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/329779/news/nation/pnoy-no-plans-to-extend-term-after-2016 |title=PNoy: No plans to extend term after 2016 |work=GMA News Online |date=2013-10-03 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\nBy May 2014, a [[Facebook]] page calling support for one more term for Aquino was launched, despite the constitutional prohibition for presidential re-election; Presidential Spokesman [[Edwin Lacierda]] said that Aquino \"listens to the voice of his bosses\" (by bosses, meaning the people).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/92745/1-more-term--pnoy-listens-to-the-voice-of-his-bosses---palace |title=1 MORE TERM? PNoy 'listens to the voice of his bosses' - Palace |first=Dexter |last=San Pedro |work=InterAksyon.com |date=2014-08-06 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> On an August 13, 2014 [[TV5 (Philippines)|TV5]] interview by [[Far Eastern University Institute of Law]] Dean [[Mel Sta. Maria]], Aquino confirmed that he is open to the possibility of running again as President in 2016 if a [[Constitutional reform in the Philippines#Aquino Administration|constitutional amendment]] lifting the presidential term limit, amongst other things, is successful.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/article/93241/video-news5-exclusive--president-aquino-says-he-is-open-to-cha-cha-2nd-term-and-a-weaker-sc |title=VIDEO, NEWS5 EXCLUSIVE President Aquino says he is open to Cha-Cha, 2nd term, and a weaker SC |work=Interaksyon.com |date=2014-08-13 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>  The Liberals openly admitted that Aquino is still their preferred candidate in the election, with Roxas only their second choice.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/374882/news/nation/lps-admit-pnoy-s-their-best-bet-in-2016-mar-only-second-best |title=LPs admit PNoy's their best bet in 2016; Mar, only second best |work=GMA News Online |date=2014-08-14 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref> Binay, for his part, said that he is \"ready\" to face anyone in the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manilatimes.net/binay-vs-pnoy-2016-looms-cha-cha-passes/119310/ |title=Binay vs PNoy in 2016 looms if Cha-cha passes |first=Rhaydz |last=Garcia |work=[[The Manila Times]] |date=2014-08-15 |accessdate=2015-05-24}}</ref>\n\nSeveral months later, Aquino explicitly ruled out a presidential campaign for him in 2016, instead urging voters to \"discern properly\" in voting.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stasiareport.com/the-big-story/asia-report/philippines/story/philippine-president-aquino-rules-out-seeking-second-ter |title=Philippine President Aquino rules out seeking second term |work=[[The Straits Times]] |date=2014-10-28 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\n====Kris Aquino====\nOn April 2, 2013, [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lingayen-Dagupan|Lingayen-Dagupan]] archbishop emeritus [[Oscar Cruz]] has asked presidential sister and actress [[Kris Aquino]]'s camp to clarify reports of her plans on running for the vice presidency because he heard of her political plans from \"credible sources within the administration.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/383725/archbishop-wants-to-know-if-rumor-is-true-kris-aquino-to-run-for-vp |title=Archbishop wants to know if rumor is true: Kris Aquino to run for VP |first=Philip C. |last=Tubeza |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |date=2013-04-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> Presidential spokesperson [[Edwin Lacierda]] denied rumors of her vice presidential candidacy and alluded to Cruz as a \"rumormonger\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/384435/palace-tells-bishop-leave-kris-aquino-alone-rumormonger |title=Palace tells bishop: Leave Kris Aquino alone, 'rumormonger' |first=Michael Lim |last=Ubac |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |date=2013-04-04 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n\nIn a March 2014 edition of her talk show ''[[Aquino & Abunda Tonight]]'', she said the possibility of her candidacy has \"never been discussed\" and added that \"it\u2019s (the election) not yet my time.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2014/03/05/1297355/kris-aquino-denies-shell-run-vice-president-2016 |title=Kris Aquino denies she'll run for Vice President in 2016 |first=Chuck |last=Smith |work=[[Philippine Star]] |date=2014-03-05 |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref>\n\n====JV Ejercito====\nIn May 2014, Senator [[JV Ejercito]] ruled out becoming the running mate of Vice President Binay and said that running for a higher post in the next elections is \"farthest\" from his mind.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/05/22/14/jv-rules-out-running-binays-vice-cites-same-skin-color |title=JV rules out running as Binay's vice, cites same skin color |first=Willard |last=Cheng |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=2014-05-22 |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref> A year later, with the emergence of [[Grace Poe]] as a possible presidential candidate, Ejercito said that \"I\u2019m in a difficult situation also because both [Poe and Binay] are very close to me.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = JV Ejercito torn between Binay, Poe|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/692392/jv-ejercito-torn-between-binay-poe|website = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate = 2015-06-07|first = Christine O.|last = Avenda\u00f1o|date = 2015-05-20}}</ref>\n\n====Jinggoy Estrada====\n[[File:Jinggoy Estrada.jpg|thumb|upright|Jinggoy Estrada]]In an oath-taking ceremony of [[Pwersa ng Masang Pilipino]] members in November 2012, [[Jinggoy Estrada]] compared himself to his father, former President and Manila Mayor Joseph Estrada. He said his father describes him as a copycat, saying he also became [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]] mayor, senator and even best actor. But after noting that his father\u2019s election to the vice presidency, he said \"It\u2019s up to you what will happen next.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/11/30/12/jinggoy-hints-he-might-become-vice-president|title=Jinggoy hints he might become vice-president|first=RG|last=Cruz|work=ABS-CBN News Online\n|date=November 30, 2012}}</ref>\n\nDespite being implicated in the PDAF scam, he believes critics cannot rule him out as a possible vice presidential candidate and still has the machinery and support to run a campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/53457-jinggoy-support-machinery-2016-bid|title=Jinggoy: I still have support, machinery for 2016|first=Ayee|last=Macaraig|work=Rappler|date=March 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Joseph Estrada====\n[[File:JosephEstradajf1486.JPG|thumb|upright|Joseph Estrada|left]]\nIn February 2014, [[Joseph Estrada]] said that he has already served as president and that his post as [[Mayor of Manila]] will be his \"last hurrah.\"<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/focus/01/10/14/erap-says-he-wont-run-president-again|title=Erap says he won't run for president again|first=Zyann|last=Ambrosio|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=February 5, 2014}}</ref> Almost a year later, Estrada said that he would run if both [[Jejomar Binay]] and [[Grace Poe]] won't run against the administration candidate. If either or both persons run, he said \"I will just be a spectator should VP Binay and Grace run against each other in the 2016 presidential elections.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/erap-may-seek-presidency-000000776.html |title=Erap may seek presidency if\u2026 |first=Jose Rodel |last=Clapano |work=[[Philippine Star]] |publisher=Yahoo! News Philippines |date=January 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, speculations arose that he might replace his son, Senator Jinggoy Estrada, as Binay\u2019s running mate due to the former\u2019s involvement in the [[PDAF scam]] but he quickly dismissed the rumor, saying he will retire from politics in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/05/27/1327779/erap-dispels-rumors-2016-vp-bid |title=Erap dispels rumors on 2016 VP bid |first=Jose Rodel |last=Calpano |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=2014-05-27 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref>  A year later, in a ''[[24 Oras]]'' interview, he said that he is keeping his options open.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/489910/news/nation/erap-not-closing-door-on-possible-third-shot-at-the-presidency |title=Erap not closing door on possible third shot at the presidency |work=GMA News Online |date=May 20, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> Estrada, after Binay proposed a Binay\u2013Estrada tandem in June 2015, Estrada said that he has no interest in running for vice president, and intends to defend the Manila mayoralty.<ref name=\"Clapano\"/>\n\nAfter being conspicuously absent at the launching of UNA, Estrada clarified that he is not a member of UNA, and is instead the head of his own PMP party, which is not in coalition with UNA. However, he said that he will run for president if Binay won't be able to run.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/07/02/1472362/erap-run-if-binay-backs-out|title = Erap to run if Binay backs out|last = |first = |date = 2015-07-02|work = [[The Philippine Star]]|access-date = 2015-07-31|via = }}</ref> By October 2015, Estrada said that he'd run for president if both Binay and Grace Poe were disqualified, to \"preserve democracy in the country\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Erap to run for president if Poe, Binay disqualified|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109137-erap-run-president-if-poe-binay-disqualified|website = Rappler|publisher = Rappler.com|accessdate = 2015-10-15|date = 2015-10-13|first = Buena|last = Bernal}}</ref>\n\n====Richard J. Gordon====\n[[File:RJGred1.JPG|thumb|upright|Dick Gordon|left]]\n[[Richard J. Gordon]] launched a presidential bid in 2010 for his own party of [[Bagumbayan-VNP]]. Gordon also launched a senatorial bid in 2013 but lost by a close margin to [[Gringo Honasan]] for the final Senate seat. Having a clean and strong track record, Gordon was a potential candidate for 2016. Gordon is a former mayor of [[Olongapo City]], former chairman of the [[Subic Bay Metropolitan Authority]], former secretary of the Department of Tourism and currently serves as chairman of the [[Philippine Red Cross]] after 45 years of volunteering.\n\n====Manny Pacquiao====\n[[File:Manny Pacquiao in Siliman.jpg|thumb|upright|Manny Pacquiao]]\nCongressman from Sarangani [[Manny Pacquiao]] said on [[DZBB-AM|DZBB]] radio during the press conference of his 2011 fight against [[Juan Manuel Marquez]] in Mexico that \"Come 2016 I am going to run (for) vice president... No more boxing at that time.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Manny Pacquiao eyes vice presidency in 2016 polls|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/231937/news/nation/manny-pacquiao-eyes-vice-presidency-in-2016-polls|website = GMA News Online|accessdate = 2015-06-07|date = 2011-09-09}}</ref> but later backtracked when he said \"No, it\u2019s not possible yet. I\u2019m not old enough\" because he will only be 37 years old during the elections \u2013 3 years short of the constitutional age requirement of 40.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/56549/pacquiao-admits-too-young-to-be-vp|title = Pacquiao admits too young to be VP|work = [[Agence France-Presse]]|date = September 10, 2011|publisher = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]}}</ref>\n\nJejomar Binay has later said that Pacquiao is one of the people UNA is eyeing for their senatorial slate.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/52417-binay-pacquiao-senator-2016|title = Binay: Pacquiao our Senate bet for 2016|last = Macaraig|first = Ayee|date = 2014-03-07|work = Rappler.com|access-date = 2015-06-07|via = }}</ref>\n\n====Panfilo Lacson====\n[[File:Sen. Panfilo M. Lacson.jpg|thumb|upright|Panfilo Lacson|left]]\nInterior and Local Government Secretary [[Mar Roxas]] acknowledged that [[Panfilo Lacson]] is qualified to run in for president, but there have been no talks on the latter joining the [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal Party]]. Despite of this, he said in February 2014 that he is \"color blind\" to politics and would rather focus on rehabilitating areas hit by [[Typhoon Yolanda]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/12/16/13/mar-ping-qualified-run-president-2016 race|title=Mar: Ping qualified to run in 2016|first=Karen|last=Davila|work=ABS-CBN News Online|date=December 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/02/15/1290725/ping-2016-presl-poll-not-mind-too-busy-yolanda|title=Ping: 2016 pres'l poll not in mind, too busy with 'Yolanda'|first=Alexis|last=Romero|work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=February 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAfter resigning as presidential assistant for recovery in February 2015, Lacson, in a press conference at the Diamond Hotel in [[Manila]], told reporters that he is \"not planning, but contemplating\" about running for the presidency. Aside from another presidential campaign, Lacson is considering a return to the Senate, while ruling out local politics.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.rappler.com/nation/83403-ping-lacson-2016-plans |title=Lacson for president in 2016? 'I'm thinking about it' |first=Angela |last=Casauay |work=[[Rappler]]|date=February 9, 2015 |accessdate=2015-02-10}}</ref> In April 2015, Lacson confirmed that he has the intention in running for president, although his final decision would depend on many factors, which he didn't elaborate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2015/04/11/1442582/lacson-eyeing-presidency-2016 |title= Lacson eyeing presidency in 2016 |first=Cecille |last=Suerte Felipe |work=[[Philippine Star]]|date=April 11, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-12}}</ref> On a press conference at [[Baguio]] a couple of weeks later, Lacson announced his intention to be an independent candidate for president.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/baguio/local-news/2015/04/24/lacson-i-may-run-president-404201 |title=Lacson: 'I may run as president'|first=Giovani Joy |last=Fontanilla |work=[[Sun.Star]] Baguio|date=April 24, 2015 |accessdate=2015-04-25}}</ref> A month later, Lacson said that he will announce his decision to run for president after the next survey is released.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://manilastandardtoday.com/2015/05/21/ping-to-wait-for-survey-before-deciding/ |title=Ping to wait for survey before deciding |first=Macon |last=Ramos-Araneta |work=[[The New Standard (newspaper)|The New Standard]] |date=May 21, 2015 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, he will no longer seek to run for president, but instead he now focused on his possible return to the senate in the coming elections.\n\n====Francis Pangilinan====\nIn May 2014, then newly appointed Presidential Adviser on Food Security and Agricultural Modernization [[Francis Pangilinan]] said that \"I'm not interested in the presidency, and I\u2019m not interested in the elections at this time.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = Pangilinan not interested in 2016 elections\u2026'at this time'|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/600106/pangilinan-not-interested-in-2016-electionsat-this-time|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-06-17|first = |last = |date = 2014-05-06}}</ref> By December 2014, a \"Poe-Kiko\", a pun on the Tagalog phrase for \"my vagina\", tandem of [[Grace Poe]] and Pangilinan was making rounds; Pangilinan describe it as \"a joke\" on the Christmas party of the National Irrigation Administration. and wished Poe \"lives up to everybody's expectations.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Poe-Kiko' team just a joke, says Pangilinan - Manila Standard Today|url = http://manilastandardtoday.com/2014/12/15/-poe-kiko-team-just-a-joke-says-pangilinan/|accessdate = 2015-06-17|date = 2014-12-15|website = [[The New Standard (Philippine newspaper)|The New Standard]]}}</ref>\n\nBy late August 2015, Pangilinan said in a budget briefing at the House of Representatives that he would announce his announce for 2016 \"after the ghost month\" of the Chinese calendar ends in September 12, with the Liberal Party looking to see him to lead the \"powerhouse\" senatorial ticket.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Kiko Pangilinan to announce 2016 plan after 'ghost month'|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/534271/news/nation/kiko-pangilinan-to-announce-2016-plan-after-ghost-month|accessdate = 2015-08-27|date = 2015-08-25|website = GMA News Online}}</ref>\n\n====Manny Pangilinan====\n[[File:Manuel_Pangilinan_2012.jpg|thumb|upright|Manny Pangilinan]]\nBy late 2010, [[Manny Pangilinan]], chairman of utility companies [[PLDT]] and [[Meralco]]. and of [[TV5 (Philippines)|TV5]], is claimed as a \"dark horse\" by political analysts.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/focus/10/06/13/mvp-dark-horse-2016-polls |title=MVP a dark horse in 2016 polls? |first=Kathlyn |last= dela Cruz |work=[[ABS-CBN]] |date=2013-10-06 |accessdate=2013-10-06}}</ref> The businessman later commented on the rumors that he would seek an elective position, saying \"there is no political blood that runs through my veins. I believe I can serve our people better some other way.\" He also said his decision was \"final\" amid encouragement from various sectors that he would make a great president, given his \"technocratic skills.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Lectura|first=Lenie|title=Exclusive: MVP: Not running in 2016|url=http://businessmirror.com.ph/index.php/en/news/top-news/20912-exclusive-mvp-not-running-in-2016|publisher=BusinessMirror}}</ref>\n\n====Bong Revilla====\n[[File:Ramon Bong Revilla.JPG|thumb|left|upright|Bong Revilla]]\nIn January 2013, then House Minority Leader Danilo Suarez, [[Lakas-CMD]] vice-chairman, said that their party is likely considering [[Bong Revilla]] to be their candidate.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/349679/lakas-cmd-grooming-bong-revilla-for-2016-presidential-race|title=Lakas-CMD grooming Bong Revilla for 2016 presidential race|first=Karen|last=Boncocan|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=January 30, 2013}}</ref> Revilla later revealed that he is open to running for president and his involvement in the [[Priority Development Assistance Fund scam]] (PDAF scam) would not affect his political ambition.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/revilla-eyes-2016-presidency/ |title=Revilla eyes 2016 presidency |first=Mario |last=Casayuran |work=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-05-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150531015702/http://www.mb.com.ph/revilla-eyes-2016-presidency/ |archivedate=2015-05-31 }}</ref>\n\nAfters being jailed at the Philippine National Police custodial center in Quezon City due to the PDAF scam, Revilla in May 2015 said that he is still open to running in 2016, as no law prohibits incarcerated people from running. When pushed further, Revilla said \"\"No comment,\" as he may not be able to \"get free: because of it.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/490774/news/nation/bong-revilla-open-to-running-for-higher-office-in-2016-polls |title=Bong Revilla open to running for higher office in 2016 polls |first=Elizabeth |last=Marcelo |work=GMA News Online |date=2015-05-23 }}</ref>\n\nWhile still in detention for his involvement in the PDAF scam, Revilla told reporters that his presidential ambition caused his detention, and that he was a \"at a loss\" on what to do once the filing of candidacies started, On his plans for the presidency, he said that \" I\u2019m not in a hurry. I\u2019m still young\", and that he wanted to clear his name first before running.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Revilla says presidential ambition caused his detention for plunder|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/726535/revilla-says-presidential-ambition-caused-his-detention-for-plunder|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-10-15|publisher = |date = 2015-09-30|first = Marc Jayson|last = Cayabyab}}</ref>\n\n====Vilma Santos====\n[[File:Vilma Santos DOH Medical Assistance for Indigent Program MOA signing (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|left|Vilma Santos]]\nVice President Binay\u2019s visit to [[Batangas]] in February 2014 fueled speculation that provincial governor [[Vilma Santos]] might be his running mate. In a later interview, he finally admitted to considering her as his vice-presidential candidate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/03/02/14/binay-considering-vilma-running-mate-2016 |title=Binay considering Vilma as running mate in 2016 |work=ABS-CBNnews.com |date=2014-03-02 |accessdate=2015-03-15}}</ref> However, her husband, Senator [[Ralph Recto]], said in March 2014 that she is not planning to run for a higher position and might retire from politics instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/581945/vilma-santos-has-no-plans-for-2016-might-retire-from-politics-sen-recto< |title=Vilma has no plans for 2016, might retire from politics\u2014Sen. Recto |first=Matikas |last=Santos |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2015-03-03 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2015, after Duterte suggested that she could be his running mate, Santos herself dismissed reports that she is running for a higher position, and echoing her husbands earlier statements, may opt to return to showbiz instead after her term ends.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/503086/news/regions/batangas-gov-vilma-santos-denies-rumors-she-will-run-in-2016-elections|title = Batangas Gov. Vilma Santos denies rumors she will run in 2016 elections|last = |first = |date = 2015-06-12|work = GMA News Online|access-date = 2015-06-17|via = }}</ref> Two months later, Santos said that if she'd run for public office in 2016, is that it would be for congresswoman from Batangas, and that she isn't running for vice president.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Vilma insists she won't run for VP|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/08/04/15/vilma-insists-she-wont-run-vp|accessdate = 2015-08-04|first = Jay|last = Ruiz|website = abs-cbnnews.com|date = 2015-08-04}}</ref>\n\n====Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.====\n[[File:Gates Teodoro Press Conference 090601 cropped3.jpg|thumb|upright|Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]]\nIn September 2014, Davao City mayor Rodrigo Duterte said that, instead of being the running mate to Senator Santiago, he wanted [[Gilberto Teodoro, Jr.]] to be his running mate.<ref name=\"INQUIRER.net\">{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/637306/poe-says-no-duterte-tells-santiago-take-gibo-teodoro |title=Poe says no; Duterte tells Santiago: Take Gibo Teodoro |work=INQUIRER.net |date=2014-09-14 |accessdate=2015-05-13}}</ref> In March 2015, [[Lakas\u2013CMD]] national president [[Ferdinand Martin Romualdez]] said that his party is preparing for the 2016 elections; [[Danilo Suarez]] also remarked that they are convincing Teodoro to go out of retirement to run anew.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/lakas-cmd-eyeing-gibo-teodoro-for-2016/ |title= Lakas-CMD eyeing 'Gibo' Teodoro for 2016  |first=Ben |last=Rosario |work=[[The Manila Bulletin]] |date=2015-03-29 |accessdate=2015-05-23}}</ref> However, Santiago chose [[Bongbong Marcos]] as her running mate in October 2015, the month after Alan Cayetano announced his bid for the vice presidency as Duterte's running mate.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|title=Miriam Santiago: Bongbong Marcos is my running mate|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/politics/elections/2016/109349-miriam-santiago-bongbong-marcos-is-my-running-mate|website=Rappler}}</ref>\n\n====Manny Villar====\n[[File:Manny Villar T'nalak Festival 2009.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Manny Villar]]\nHis wife, Senator [[Cynthia Villar]], did not rule the possibility of him running for president again, saying in March 2014 \"You know, for [[Manny Villar|Manny]], presidency is destiny for him after 2010. He said if it\u2019s meant for you, then it will come. If not, then it won\u2019t come.\"<ref>{{cite news|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/589202/villar-may-run-again-for-president-says-wife|title = Villar may run again for president, says wife|work = Inquirer.net|date = March 26, 2014|first = Maila|last = Ager|access-date = 2015-06-01}}</ref> Later, that year, when [[Jejomar Binay]] identified the former senator as a potential running mate, Cynthia said that \"Villar is not running for vice president. Never.\"<ref name=\"Rappler.com\"/>\n\nIn May 2015, Trillanes pushed for Villar to run anew,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Trillanes pushing NP leader Villar for another presidential run|url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/483498/news/nation/trillanes-pushing-np-leader-villar-for-another-presidential-run|accessdate = 2015-05-30|date = 2015-05-07|website = GMA News Online|last = Sisante|first = Johanna Camille}}</ref> while his Villar's wife Cynthia said that the Nacionalistas failed to agree on their plans for 2016 during their Manila-Japan cruise, citing that it's too early to decide on plans for 2016 as the cause.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title = NP fails to reach consensus on 2016 poll plans|url = http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/689202/np-fails-to-reach-consensus-on-2016-poll-plans|website = INQUIRER.net|accessdate = 2015-05-30|first = Maila|last = Ager}}</ref> By October, Villar's son [[Mark Villar|Mark]], also the representative from Las Pi\u00f1as, said that \"My father's definitely not running next election\", adding that the elder Villar was enjoying his time as a businessman.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Manny Villar won't run in 2016, son says|url = http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/10/09/15/manny-villar-wont-run-2016-son-says|website = ABS-CBN News|accessdate = 2015-10-15|last = Cruz|first = RG|date = 2015-10-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{2016 Philippine elections}}\n\n[[Category:Candidates in the 2016 Philippine presidential election| ]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced: Vice President \u2192 vice president,typo(s) fixed: President \u2192 president (7), \u2019s \u2192 's (4), 3-0 \u2192 3\u20130, etc.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_candidates_in_the_2016_Philippine_presidential_election"}
